22
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:32,276
Moscow, the fifties...
It seems like it was yesterday...

23
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:36,909
Oh, come on:
30 years have passed!

24
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:41,915
But if I close my eyes,
I can clearly see...

25
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:51,073
This guy vrooming on the bike
with Savransky is me.

26
00:03:51,760 --> 00:03:54,593
As you can see, I am very young.

27
00:03:54,760 --> 00:03:57,991
I came to Moscow and studied
at the university there.

28
00:03:58,920 --> 00:04:02,435
The moment I saw Moscow
I came to love it.

29
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:07,675
It embraced me passionately
with its Boulevard Ring,

30
00:04:07,840 --> 00:04:09,990
with its Garden Ring:

31
00:04:10,440 --> 00:04:14,831
it beckoned me into its streets,
into its curving by-streets,

32
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:19,994
until it left me be, totally
dumbfounded, to have some rest

33
00:04:20,520 --> 00:04:23,830
in a communal flat
near the Pokrovsky Gates.

34
00:04:24,200 --> 00:04:28,830
THE POKROVSKY GATES

35
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:33,991
This is my auntie.

36
00:04:42,680 --> 00:04:44,671
Coming.

37
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:51,677
My auntie Alice,
a noble-hearted refined woman,

38
00:04:51,840 --> 00:04:55,071
kindly sheltered me, her nephew.

39
00:04:56,000 --> 00:05:01,199
Hello?
You want to speak with Kostya?

40
00:05:01,440 --> 00:05:04,830
Your humble servant, my nephew,
is still sleeping.

41
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:07,992
He came home only at dawn.

42
00:05:12,320 --> 00:05:16,916
Be so kind to leave your number.
Just a second, I'll take a pencil.

43
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:20,355
One moment.

44
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:23,591
Lev Evghenievich!

45
00:05:24,440 --> 00:05:28,194
Well... Oh Jesus!

46
00:05:29,760 --> 00:05:34,754
1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8...

47
00:05:34,920 --> 00:05:39,277
Lev Evghenievich dear,
you stole the pencil again!

48
00:05:39,440 --> 00:05:43,274
14, 15, 16, 17, 18, 19, 21, 21,

49
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:49,357
22, 23, 24, 25, 26, 27, 28, 29,

50
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:54,992
30, 31, 32, 33, 34, 35...

51
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:58,992
Yes, my dear?..

52
00:05:59,840 --> 00:06:03,753
42, 43, 44, 45, 46, 47,

53
00:06:03,920 --> 00:06:08,755
48, 49, 50, 51, 52, 53...

54
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:12,191
Some culinarian!

55
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:24,199
Savva, the breakfast is ready!

56
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:27,352
Call Khobotov, let him come too.

57
00:06:27,520 --> 00:06:30,512
Sehr gut', Margarita Pavlovna.

58
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:37,199
Lev Evghenievich! Did you hear?
Go and have some breakfast!

59
00:06:39,760 --> 00:06:43,514
Margarita Pavlovna Khobotova -
a woman of imposing virtues.

60
00:06:43,680 --> 00:06:47,355
At that time she turned over
a new leaf in her life.

61
00:06:47,520 --> 00:06:50,432
She was preparing herself for
a new marriage - with Savva Efimov.

62
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:52,989
'Danke schon', Margarita Pavlovna.

63
00:06:54,200 --> 00:06:57,431
But her ex-husband,
Lev Evghenievich Khobotov,

64
00:06:57,600 --> 00:07:00,751
shared their daily
repast all the same.

65
00:07:00,920 --> 00:07:03,912
It was a triple unity, and
it aroused my quick interest.

66
00:07:04,200 --> 00:07:07,192
- You don't eat enough.
- Thanks, I don't feel like eating.

67
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:10,591
What do you mean? You should
fill yourself in the morning,

68
00:07:10,760 --> 00:07:13,194
'cause brains need energy too.

69
00:07:15,920 --> 00:07:20,994
And my lastmost neighbor -
an artiste Arkady Velyurov.

70
00:07:23,640 --> 00:07:26,359
He was a stand-up comedian...

71
00:07:37,520 --> 00:07:42,674
'So here I am, before all of ye,
A serious and a funny guy.

72
00:07:42,840 --> 00:07:48,198
'I make no bones of telling ye:
Who, how & what & when & why...

73
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:54,435
'Hey, stop the war, keep saying we.
Thus humour - is a remedy.

74
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:59,833
'A storm without? - 'tis no big deal.
Our sense of humour makes it still.

75
00:08:06,320 --> 00:08:11,678
'The USA had quite a shock:
Is Eisenhower a hawk?

76
00:08:11,840 --> 00:08:17,437
'Guys, I'm all for peace', he lied.
Oh what a cunning proselyte!

77
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:23,516
'Sing, sing nightingales!
Spring, spring in the veins.

78
00:08:23,840 --> 00:08:30,598
'War-loving viper hisses and stings!
But Dove spreads its wings!

79
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:37,352
Did you like my punch lines?

80
00:08:37,520 --> 00:08:41,195
Thank you very much,
my dear Muscovites,

81
00:08:41,360 --> 00:08:46,514
and guests of our city, for having
come on a rendezvous with an artiste.

82
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:51,437
We're having the rain in the street,
but you're having fun at my concert.

83
00:08:51,760 --> 00:08:54,991
The jokes are showering...

84
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:59,352
It's autumn now in Moscow, friends,
a fine and beautiful autumn.

85
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:04,913
But the Soviet barometers
can only show 'clear sky'!

86
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:08,593
Switch on the radio,
and you will hear:

87
00:09:08,760 --> 00:09:11,832
'Clear sky in Moscow -
compared to the London fog...'.

88
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:15,356
I do hope, my dear friends...

89
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:18,910
That one nice day,
we'll hear on the radio:

90
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:23,198
'It's a clear sky worldwide,
the fog has melted away!'

91
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:30,673
I'm pleased to see
more people coming here,

92
00:09:30,840 --> 00:09:34,355
not with standing
the inclement weather.

93
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:40,597
Specially for them I'll perform
another couplet of my friend,

94
00:09:40,760 --> 00:09:42,751
whom I don't hesitate to call

95
00:09:42,920 --> 00:09:46,754
the great poet Soev!
Give him a round of applause!

96
00:09:56,520 --> 00:10:00,513
'A jazz-band made such a knack,
That I had a heart attack.

97
00:10:00,680 --> 00:10:04,593
'Boogie-woogie: do you like it? -
But I nearly kicked the bucket.

98
00:10:04,760 --> 00:10:06,751
Great!

99
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:13,598
'There was once a bum who died,
All his bum-friends bitterly cried.

100
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:18,994
'And two punks, right on his grave,
made a boogie-woogie rave!'

101
00:10:34,360 --> 00:10:36,999
Sveta! Sveta!

102
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:41,991
Gladkova! Gladkova!

103
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:46,910
Sveta! Sveta!

104
00:10:58,840 --> 00:11:03,436
I hope you remember me:
Arkady Velyurov, a stand-up artiste.

105
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:06,997
Wow...

106
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:11,432
'Firmas e bankas latino-amerikanos...

107
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:22,432
'Latino-amerikanos economi...'

108
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:29,999
Yes?

109
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:34,909
- Khobotov, what does that mean?
- I just took your hair-dryer.

110
00:11:37,760 --> 00:11:41,355
Are you going out? Don't forget,
we're having guests today.

111
00:11:41,520 --> 00:11:45,752
- Let Savva entertain them.
- Please, don't be late.

112
00:11:45,920 --> 00:11:48,593
I can't promise you that.

113
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:52,839
You bring only discomfort to me...

114
00:12:28,680 --> 00:12:29,999
Kostya!

115
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:33,593
We have won!

116
00:12:34,200 --> 00:12:35,428
Oh no, you haven't.

117
00:12:46,840 --> 00:12:48,990
Yasha, come and join us.

118
00:12:52,680 --> 00:12:54,989
Oh, shucks.

119
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:09,351
Savva Ignatievich,
go and do some shopping!

120
00:13:09,520 --> 00:13:12,512
We're having guests today,
the Orloviches.

121
00:13:12,760 --> 00:13:16,435
Funf Minuten', Margarita Pavlovna.
My old buddy came to see me.

122
00:13:20,440 --> 00:13:24,353
So, you are a complete family
guy now, aren't ye?

123
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:27,832
As a matter of fact I am.
We're going to get married soon.

124
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:30,998
How it happened,
between the two of ye?

125
00:13:31,200 --> 00:13:34,351
Yes, Savva, give us
a clean breast of things.

126
00:13:34,520 --> 00:13:39,674
We lived next door during
the summer season.

127
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:44,910
I rented a room in a dacha.
So they lived next door.

128
00:13:45,520 --> 00:13:49,991
So how it all developed?
Little by little?

129
00:13:50,760 --> 00:13:55,197
You see...
Her ex, Lev Evghenievich,

130
00:13:55,360 --> 00:13:58,591
is a phenomenal person!

131
00:13:59,440 --> 00:14:02,432
He is a very learned guy, you know.

132
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:05,592
He speaks languages as a birdie
would sing its songs.

133
00:14:05,760 --> 00:14:09,833
But for the same reason he has
lack of balance in his head.

134
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:12,594
When in town, he can manage so-so.

135
00:14:12,760 --> 00:14:16,992
But when he had to face Nature,
he appeared a complete nincompoop.

136
00:14:17,200 --> 00:14:19,998
First, they charged him the double
price for the dacha room.

137
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:23,192
The passports - their
registration was overdue.

138
00:14:23,360 --> 00:14:28,514
His razor burnt down because
of the voltage difference there.

139
00:14:28,680 --> 00:14:30,671
The same thing happened
to their flat iron.

140
00:14:30,840 --> 00:14:34,196
Every time he'd short-circuit smth.
And the dacha in complete darkness.

141
00:14:34,360 --> 00:14:37,989
- His wife all in tears...
- And presto - there you are.

142
00:14:38,200 --> 00:14:43,593
Nothing of this kind on my mind.
It was just breaking my heart.

143
00:14:43,760 --> 00:14:48,914
To see a fabulously clever woman,
a specialist on South America,

144
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:54,354
so energetic - a real commander!
And losing her heart...

145
00:14:54,840 --> 00:15:00,597
I was like babysitting him.
He breaks things, I repair them.

146
00:15:00,760 --> 00:15:03,433
Ha, you're such a smart alec!

147
00:15:03,600 --> 00:15:08,594
Yeah, Savva, you've broken
a close-knit Soviet family.

148
00:15:08,760 --> 00:15:11,752
You've trampled to ashes
the family hearth.

149
00:15:11,920 --> 00:15:14,912
Kostya, don't give me that too!
It was not my initiative!

150
00:15:19,520 --> 00:15:23,513
Once Lev Evghenievich left for town.

151
00:15:23,680 --> 00:15:26,752
He promised to be back by dinner,
but he didn't come back.

152
00:15:26,920 --> 00:15:29,832
He came neither by supper, nor
by breakfast, nor the next morning.

153
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:35,199
At this junction
she became so fidgety.

154
00:15:35,360 --> 00:15:38,591
And in the evening, when I tried
to calm her down, she said:

155
00:15:38,760 --> 00:15:41,558
'Stay with me, Savva Ignatievich.'

156
00:15:41,760 --> 00:15:43,432
And you?

157
00:15:43,840 --> 00:15:46,593
I stood 'at attention', of course,

158
00:15:54,600 --> 00:15:56,750
We've been together since.

159
00:15:57,440 --> 00:16:02,195
They have an apartment being built
for them. We'll move in by spring.

160
00:16:02,360 --> 00:16:05,432
So you'll live in his apartment?

161
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:08,751
So what? It's their decision.
I only know my soldier's business.

162
00:16:08,920 --> 00:16:09,989
Bingo!

163
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:12,998
Savva, go to the shop now!

164
00:16:14,760 --> 00:16:17,752
Our guys speak warmly about you.

165
00:16:17,920 --> 00:16:20,992
You were a second to none engraver.

166
00:16:21,200 --> 00:16:23,668
Now I teach others.

167
00:16:23,840 --> 00:16:27,435
She says: "You'd rather be a teacher,
it's more respectable."

168
00:16:27,600 --> 00:16:32,196
She knows best, I guess.
But you were a first-class engraver!

169
00:16:32,360 --> 00:16:35,432
I'm afraid I'm losing my hand now.
A man without a craft is nothing.

170
00:16:35,600 --> 00:16:38,910
Take, for example, Lev Evghenievich.

171
00:16:59,280 --> 00:17:00,429
...Thanks.

172
00:17:02,800 --> 00:17:08,352
Oh, thanks.
It felt great.

173
00:17:08,520 --> 00:17:10,909
I'm glad to hear this.

174
00:17:17,960 --> 00:17:22,351
- You did it so...you know...
- Oh really?

175
00:17:24,920 --> 00:17:29,357
- It was a masterpiece of a shot!
- Oh, come on...

176
00:17:29,520 --> 00:17:32,830
- I didn't feel anything.
- Too bad.

177
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:38,518
No, I meant the place
where you inserted the syringe.

178
00:17:38,680 --> 00:17:41,194
As for the rest, it did
touch my feelings.

179
00:17:41,360 --> 00:17:43,999
But today you had
your last injection.

180
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:48,193
Don't say that. I beg you!

181
00:17:48,360 --> 00:17:53,992
I've got used to coming here,
to seeing you.

182
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:58,595
I've got used to your hands,

183
00:17:59,840 --> 00:18:02,991
to the features of your face,
to your mimicry.

184
00:18:03,680 --> 00:18:06,194
There is nothing special about me.

185
00:18:06,360 --> 00:18:11,434
Oh, how wrong you are,
how wrong!

186
00:18:12,360 --> 00:18:16,433
You remember my first coming here?

187
00:18:17,440 --> 00:18:20,193
- You forgot the referral.
- Oh yes!

188
00:18:20,360 --> 00:18:24,353
Any other woman would have
sent me away, but you...

189
00:18:25,440 --> 00:18:30,833
- Allow me to kiss your hand.
- Oh, please don't.

190
00:18:31,520 --> 00:18:34,751
Just to kiss your hand a farewell.

191
00:18:41,680 --> 00:18:45,275
Yes? Close the door!

192
00:18:45,520 --> 00:18:48,830
- For how more long?
- Close the door and wait.

193
00:18:52,920 --> 00:18:56,276
- Do I keep you from working?
- Oh, not at all.

194
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:00,991
It's autumn now already.

195
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:05,351
Soon it will be raining,
the wind will start howling...

196
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:09,513
The season of influenza!
You should keep your feet warm.

197
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:13,356
Thank you. Oh how I thank you!

198
00:19:14,760 --> 00:19:18,514
Doesn't your wife
take care of you?

199
00:19:18,680 --> 00:19:21,513
My wife? You see, she is...

200
00:19:22,360 --> 00:19:27,593
She is a very busy person, she lives
an intensive spiritual life...

201
00:19:27,760 --> 00:19:30,991
Besides, we've parted our ways.

202
00:19:31,360 --> 00:19:35,911
- She went away?
- Not in the strict sense of it, but...

203
00:19:37,480 --> 00:19:39,994
...she just stepped out.
- God Almighty!

204
00:19:40,200 --> 00:19:43,351
- She fell in love with another guy.
- For crying outloud!

205
00:19:43,520 --> 00:19:47,752
'What is there left to a lover?
A farewell word. Slowly dies

206
00:19:47,920 --> 00:19:53,995
'A fire of Indian summer.
Then - silence, thin layers of ice...'

207
00:19:54,200 --> 00:19:56,760
A verse? Did you write it?

208
00:19:56,920 --> 00:20:00,629
No, someone else.
He died of consumption.

209
00:20:00,800 --> 00:20:06,432
- How horrible!
- I'd like to see you again.

210
00:20:07,360 --> 00:20:10,352
But I don't know where
we can see each other.

211
00:20:10,520 --> 00:20:12,511
Well, there are places.

212
00:20:13,520 --> 00:20:16,592
There is a laboratory on the corner.

213
00:20:16,760 --> 00:20:18,830
People bring their tests there...

214
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:23,198
If you don't mind,
I'll be waiting for you there.

215
00:20:23,520 --> 00:20:24,953
Have you finished?

216
00:20:28,760 --> 00:20:32,753
- You're being very popular.
- No, vitamin injections are.

217
00:20:32,920 --> 00:20:35,992
Too many neurological patients.
We're scarce of the personnel.

218
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:40,751
What about our date?

219
00:20:43,600 --> 00:20:46,194
All right. After I finish work.

220
00:20:46,600 --> 00:20:48,192
Oh, thank you!

221
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:53,592
Thank you very much!

222
00:21:03,520 --> 00:21:06,193
- Well?
- Get undressed!..

223
00:21:07,440 --> 00:21:11,991
'So here I am, before all of ye,
A serious and a funny guy...'

224
00:21:12,360 --> 00:21:15,989
Kostya, it's for you.
What do I tell them?

225
00:21:16,200 --> 00:21:18,919
Let them call later.
Thanks.

226
00:21:24,840 --> 00:21:28,992
I'm sorry, my dear,
but Kostya is a bit busy now.

227
00:21:29,200 --> 00:21:31,191
He is taking a shower.

228
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:36,676
Will you please leave your telephone
number. I'll take it down.

229
00:21:36,840 --> 00:21:41,118
One second, I'll take the pencil.
Dictate!..

230
00:21:41,320 --> 00:21:44,596
Could you be a little more quiet -
I'm working with an author!

231
00:21:45,440 --> 00:21:48,671
I'm sorry, I'm very sorry.
Dictate!

232
00:21:48,880 --> 00:21:50,996
Soev, my dear friend...

233
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:57,993
- What does that all mean?
- It's Savva Ignatievich working.

234
00:21:58,200 --> 00:22:00,191
No, I didn't speak to you.
Dictate!

235
00:22:00,360 --> 00:22:03,193
He is wrong to think
we have a workshop here!

236
00:22:03,360 --> 00:22:09,196
Soev, my dear friend,
please, just hump yourself.

237
00:22:09,360 --> 00:22:11,351
You're a great talent.

238
00:22:11,520 --> 00:22:14,353
I don't know what you want from me.

239
00:22:14,520 --> 00:22:18,991
- You want too much.
- It's my style.

240
00:22:19,200 --> 00:22:23,352
Yes, but remember
how you failed too.

241
00:22:23,520 --> 00:22:27,513
Temperament - yes, but at the same
time - austere expressive means.

242
00:22:28,280 --> 00:22:31,272
Well, I'll talk with
my wife about this.

243
00:22:31,440 --> 00:22:34,989
My regards to Olga Yanovna.
I'll be waiting for you on Tuesday.

244
00:22:37,600 --> 00:22:41,593
He likes everything he writes.
It's all because of his wifey.

245
00:22:42,000 --> 00:22:47,757
She is his evil genius,
she is burning incense to him.

246
00:22:47,920 --> 00:22:50,514
All right. I shall tell him.

247
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:55,754
Dear Alice, you just
dote on your Kostya.

248
00:22:56,200 --> 00:22:59,272
You became sort of
his personal secretary.

249
00:22:59,440 --> 00:23:01,749
You encourage these
ladies' hullabaloo.

250
00:23:01,920 --> 00:23:05,993
Arkady Varlamovich,
but it is so simple!

251
00:23:06,200 --> 00:23:12,196
The boy came to Moscow.
New acquaintances, new temptations.

252
00:23:12,360 --> 00:23:17,753
Of course there appear women
who're too eager to chaperon him.

253
00:23:19,600 --> 00:23:23,354
'Sing, sing, nightingales,
Spring, spring in the veins...'

254
00:23:24,200 --> 00:23:29,991
No, he is questionable!
I wouldn't give him too much rope.

255
00:23:30,840 --> 00:23:32,990
'War-loving viper
hisses and stings...'

256
00:23:33,200 --> 00:23:37,591
Me and my auntie, we're pure
souls. You wouldn't understand.

257
00:23:37,760 --> 00:23:39,830
A telephone number
of a mysterious lass.

258
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:42,992
Who can it be? I can't remember.

259
00:23:43,360 --> 00:23:46,352
- Boo!
- Too many things on my mind.

260
00:23:46,520 --> 00:23:48,909
I study at the History department,
moonlighting too -

261
00:23:49,080 --> 00:23:52,516
an instructor at the athletics club.

262
00:23:53,280 --> 00:23:55,191
Selling your body?

263
00:23:55,360 --> 00:23:58,591
- Will you have something to eat?
- I wouldn't object to that, auntie.

264
00:24:02,080 --> 00:24:05,356
Maybe I should get on the horn to her,
just for the kicks of it..

265
00:24:07,440 --> 00:24:10,352
- Ah, no, let her relax.
- Tartuffe!

266
00:24:33,200 --> 00:24:36,749
- Arkady Velyurov home?
- Home he is.

267
00:24:36,920 --> 00:24:40,595
- You're what, his son?
- Honey, I'm his step-father.

268
00:24:40,760 --> 00:24:42,910
I wouldn't buy that.

269
00:24:43,080 --> 00:24:47,596
Well, this is my cross to bear.
Arkady Varlamovich, it's for you!

270
00:24:47,760 --> 00:24:50,832
- Good afternoon.
- Jesus, what a surprise!

271
00:24:51,440 --> 00:24:54,432
One moment, I'll just
put something on...

272
00:24:55,000 --> 00:24:59,596
- Meanwhile, may I make a call?
- Absolutely, my dear Sveta!

273
00:25:01,840 --> 00:25:06,675
So, you are Sveta. My stepson
is just crazy about you.

274
00:25:06,840 --> 00:25:10,594
Your stepson? I'm not
some babe in the wood for you.

275
00:25:10,760 --> 00:25:13,593
My name is Constantine,
which means 'constant'.

276
00:25:13,760 --> 00:25:15,751
- My congratulations to your wife.
- I'm as lonely as Robinson Crusoe.

277
00:25:15,920 --> 00:25:18,753
- The worse for you.
- I'm not as lucky as you are.

278
00:25:18,920 --> 00:25:20,911
I've known him only for 3 days.

279
00:25:21,080 --> 00:25:23,594
- So where did you meet him?
- At the swimming competitions.

280
00:25:23,760 --> 00:25:26,115
Wow, Velyurov was swimming too?!

281
00:25:26,760 --> 00:25:30,070
He was watching.
I came the second.

282
00:25:30,280 --> 00:25:32,999
The 'Labour Reserves' Club?

283
00:25:33,200 --> 00:25:35,191
- How do you know?
- Intuition.

284
00:25:35,360 --> 00:25:38,830
- He calls you Mermaid.
- He sent me a wire.

285
00:25:39,000 --> 00:25:41,514
- 'cause I have no telephone.
- What is in the wire?

286
00:25:41,680 --> 00:25:45,832
- 'Pining away'. Great.
- Really?

287
00:25:46,360 --> 00:25:48,999
You've made a good choice.

288
00:25:49,800 --> 00:25:52,917
He is a man with a scope and...
I'm sorry.

289
00:25:53,080 --> 00:25:55,833
Sveta, would you come in?

290
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:58,753
I can't. Have you got the tickets?

291
00:25:58,920 --> 00:26:00,990
I've lost my head, really!

292
00:26:04,600 --> 00:26:06,909
Show me the telegram.
I couldn't read the address.

293
00:26:07,080 --> 00:26:09,196
- Why do you need it?
- I just need it.

294
00:26:09,360 --> 00:26:11,590
- But why?
- I'll explain it to you later.

295
00:26:12,600 --> 00:26:15,990
'All your life may go to pieces
Like a castle on the sand.

296
00:26:16,680 --> 00:26:19,194
'You're pretty - for wrong kisses,
You're clever - just offhand...'

297
00:26:19,440 --> 00:26:21,192
- Tomorrow at 7 p.m.
- Thanks.

298
00:26:21,360 --> 00:26:24,079
- Shall we meet after the concert?
- Only if it is not too late.

299
00:26:24,920 --> 00:26:26,831
Oh my naiad...

300
00:26:42,440 --> 00:26:44,431
What did you tell her?

301
00:26:44,600 --> 00:26:47,592
I was just entertaining her, while
you were putting on your trousers!

302
00:26:47,760 --> 00:26:50,194
You can't have anything
in common with Sveta!

303
00:26:50,360 --> 00:26:52,430
- How do you know?
- What?!

304
00:26:53,200 --> 00:26:54,997
Yes? It's for you.

305
00:26:57,200 --> 00:27:02,911
Yes. Who is speaking?
llya? What a surprise.

306
00:27:03,080 --> 00:27:05,355
Yes, I know.

307
00:27:06,840 --> 00:27:10,753
Ha, that's a pretty kettle of fish!

308
00:27:11,360 --> 00:27:14,591
The stage was like
'home sweet home' to me,

309
00:27:14,760 --> 00:27:18,196
and now it has turned
into a Golgotha!

310
00:27:18,360 --> 00:27:22,194
But who is not drinking?
Tell me!

311
00:27:22,360 --> 00:27:26,990
Enough of it.
You just spit into my soul!

312
00:27:27,200 --> 00:27:30,829
- They care about you.
- Oh, I know what they're worth.

313
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:35,278
You must drop this bad habit.
It's a bit damp here.

314
00:27:35,440 --> 00:27:38,671
Arkady Varlamovich, what
about wetting our whistles?

315
00:27:41,840 --> 00:27:44,991
Mind, you said it.

316
00:27:45,840 --> 00:27:47,193
Let's go.

317
00:28:18,840 --> 00:28:21,752
This umbrella is such a maverick.

318
00:28:21,920 --> 00:28:25,833
- You're like a child.
- But meanwhile...

319
00:28:27,440 --> 00:28:30,000
I am 43 years old.

320
00:28:30,200 --> 00:28:34,591
- And you lost your referral...
- Yes, it was so ridiculous.

321
00:29:01,200 --> 00:29:05,352
I was afraid you wouldn't come.

322
00:29:05,520 --> 00:29:08,193
- You mean you're so lonely?
- Well, you know...

323
00:29:08,360 --> 00:29:13,514
'Oh bitter recollections, once again
you enter my desolate house...'

324
00:29:13,680 --> 00:29:16,831
- Is it your verse?
- No, it's Camoens.

325
00:29:17,000 --> 00:29:19,992
- He is dead already.
- God Almighty!

326
00:29:20,200 --> 00:29:23,192
- He died in the 16th century.
- In the 16th century?

327
00:29:23,360 --> 00:29:29,276
His is a very sad biography.
He was a soldier, he had lost his eye.

328
00:29:30,360 --> 00:29:34,069
- Then he died a pauper...
- Oh my!

329
00:29:35,280 --> 00:29:38,590
Jesus, you're such a tender heart...

330
00:30:13,360 --> 00:30:15,351
Give me the way, please...

331
00:30:15,520 --> 00:30:17,590
Ladies first...

332
00:30:29,080 --> 00:30:31,514
Please, pass the fare...

333
00:30:32,760 --> 00:30:34,990
Shucks, this umbrella again...

334
00:30:35,920 --> 00:30:37,990
- What's the matter?
- I've hurt my finger.

335
00:30:38,200 --> 00:30:40,589
- Your handkerchief is clean?
- Comparatively.

336
00:30:40,760 --> 00:30:44,514
Then you'd better take mine.
We must bandage your finger.

337
00:30:52,600 --> 00:30:55,592
- Please, sit down.
- Oh no, I don't need this.

338
00:30:55,760 --> 00:30:59,992
- We must show respect to old people.
- Thank you, young lady.

339
00:31:00,200 --> 00:31:03,829
- Lyuda, please, sit down.
- No, I can't, Lev Evghenievich.

340
00:31:04,000 --> 00:31:06,992
- Please...
- But I can't.

341
00:31:07,200 --> 00:31:09,191
Lyuda, but please.

342
00:31:41,080 --> 00:31:44,436
Oh, how many books you have.
You must be a professor!

343
00:31:44,680 --> 00:31:50,277
I work at the publishing house.
I edit foreign poetry.

344
00:31:55,200 --> 00:31:59,751
Camo... Camoens...
The one that had lost his eye?

345
00:31:59,920 --> 00:32:03,993
And Cervantes had lost his hand.

346
00:32:04,200 --> 00:32:07,829
Oh stop it. This is too much!

347
00:32:08,000 --> 00:32:10,594
We can't help it. It's life.

348
00:32:14,600 --> 00:32:16,591
We are waiting for you!

349
00:32:16,760 --> 00:32:20,514
Is this Savva Ignatievich?
Nina Andreevna.

350
00:32:20,680 --> 00:32:22,591
Thanks.

351
00:32:23,200 --> 00:32:25,350
Good evening, dear colleague.

352
00:32:26,000 --> 00:32:29,197
- A little surprise.
- Come on in.

353
00:32:29,760 --> 00:32:34,754
Savva, tell Khobotov
the Orloviches are here.

354
00:32:34,920 --> 00:32:36,831
Javol, Margarita Pavlovna.

355
00:32:37,760 --> 00:32:41,355
Your Savva is a pleasant guy.

356
00:32:41,520 --> 00:32:46,833
He was an artist of metal work,
now he is an instructor.

357
00:32:50,440 --> 00:32:55,275
How is he getting on with your ex?

358
00:32:55,440 --> 00:33:00,355
He likes him very much.
You can't but like Khobotov.

359
00:33:02,840 --> 00:33:08,995
And what does Lev Evghenievich
make of all this?

360
00:33:09,200 --> 00:33:12,192
He gives Savva his dues, of course.

361
00:33:12,920 --> 00:33:16,993
Oh, highly spiritual relations!

362
00:33:17,360 --> 00:33:21,592
'A beggar seeking alms you are,
An outcast by all forsaken.

363
00:33:21,760 --> 00:33:27,676
'So feeling sore your poor heart:
And bitter death would be a welcome.'

364
00:33:27,840 --> 00:33:29,831
- Is this a Camoens too?
- No.

365
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:33,436
It's Francois Villon,
his poem 'Testament'.

366
00:33:33,600 --> 00:33:38,594
- He died too?
- He was hanged or stabbed, whatever.

367
00:33:38,760 --> 00:33:44,198
My! Do these things
happen to all poets?

368
00:33:44,360 --> 00:33:46,590
Almost to all of them.

369
00:33:52,840 --> 00:33:55,991
Look, Lev Evghenievich,
the Orloviches are here.

370
00:33:56,200 --> 00:33:58,998
- So what?
- Don't be like that.

371
00:33:59,200 --> 00:34:01,668
- I told you: I can't.
- She wants you to come.

372
00:34:01,840 --> 00:34:04,752
- I am busy.
- She warned you in the morning.

373
00:34:04,920 --> 00:34:07,275
I told 'no' in the morning.

374
00:34:07,440 --> 00:34:10,989
- So you will not come?
- No.

375
00:34:11,200 --> 00:34:13,509
- You'll upset Margarita Pavlovna.
- I am sorry.

376
00:34:13,680 --> 00:34:14,908
For shame!

377
00:34:15,080 --> 00:34:20,996
Thanks to you I understood
one shouldn't be afraid to live.

378
00:34:21,200 --> 00:34:23,998
- There is nothing to be afraid of!
-...One shouldn't postpone things...

379
00:34:24,200 --> 00:34:27,431
'We're buried in the pits and graves,
And not a chance the dead to raise...'

380
00:34:27,600 --> 00:34:30,512
- It's Francois...
- No, it's Arthur Rimbaud.

381
00:34:30,680 --> 00:34:33,592
He died in the 19th century: he was
very talented and very hapless.

382
00:34:33,760 --> 00:34:36,194
- And he too?!
- He had had his foot amputated.

383
00:34:36,760 --> 00:34:39,433
As if they did it on purpose!..

384
00:34:39,600 --> 00:34:43,513
lndeed... I see your lips
are trembling.

385
00:34:43,680 --> 00:34:47,195
- I could show you a polka dance.
- You can dance?

386
00:34:47,360 --> 00:34:52,514
It's an old French folksong,
very naive.

387
00:34:53,920 --> 00:34:58,516
'Rosamund, now
we have finished the war!

388
00:34:59,600 --> 00:35:04,435
'Rosamund, I've nothing
to do anymore.

389
00:35:05,440 --> 00:35:10,355
'Rosamund, my country
is waiting for me.

390
00:35:11,200 --> 00:35:16,354
'So farewell, Rosamund,
I'm going back to my family!

391
00:35:16,840 --> 00:35:19,832
'Hey, we shall don
the neckties now...'

392
00:35:20,440 --> 00:35:24,752
- He is very original, isn't he.
- There is something primeval in him.

393
00:35:55,760 --> 00:36:00,197
- What's going on?
- They imitate the French stars.

394
00:36:00,360 --> 00:36:03,670
Oh yeah, it's very obliging.

395
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:09,992
- When will you come?
- I don't know, my angel.

396
00:36:10,200 --> 00:36:13,192
Nights are full of surprises,
aren't they?

397
00:36:14,680 --> 00:36:19,993
One day your Kostya will surprise you
to a very great extent.

398
00:36:20,440 --> 00:36:24,672
Why don't you watch the film?
You high priest of the Muses.

399
00:36:26,920 --> 00:36:29,673
I'm a high priest
of stand-up comedy!

400
00:36:42,520 --> 00:36:44,829
- How wonderful!
- You liked it?

401
00:36:46,600 --> 00:36:49,910
Somebody is knocking!

402
00:36:55,200 --> 00:37:01,355
What does this all mean?
The Orloviches are waiting.

403
00:37:01,520 --> 00:37:05,195
But in what way should it
concern me?

404
00:37:05,360 --> 00:37:08,352
- Khobotov, don't be so petty!
- I have always hated them!

405
00:37:08,520 --> 00:37:13,833
- You're in blinkers of prejudice!
- Excuse me, I'm having guests.

406
00:37:14,280 --> 00:37:19,195
- Oh really? How many of them?
- It doesn't matter.

407
00:37:19,360 --> 00:37:22,352
Velyurov told me smth about this.
She works in a kindergarten?

408
00:37:22,520 --> 00:37:24,988
Your Velyurov is a gossiper.

409
00:37:25,200 --> 00:37:28,749
Ah, there you are. You are having
a rendezvous here?

410
00:37:28,920 --> 00:37:31,593
- Margo, stop it.
- What did she find in you?

411
00:37:31,760 --> 00:37:35,514
With all your infantility you are
too cumbersome for a kindergarten.

412
00:37:35,680 --> 00:37:38,592
She is a medical worker,
and I'm a grown-up person.

413
00:37:38,760 --> 00:37:41,672
A grown-up person? You'll be
lost without me and Savva.

414
00:37:41,840 --> 00:37:44,991
- I don't think so.
- You, 'enfant terrible'!

415
00:37:45,200 --> 00:37:47,998
- No!
- Khobotov, keep your hair on!

416
00:37:51,520 --> 00:37:53,750
- Well, hello.
- Hi.

417
00:37:53,920 --> 00:37:57,993
- So, you are Raissa?
- Lyudmila.

418
00:37:58,200 --> 00:38:00,430
I knew as well.

419
00:38:00,600 --> 00:38:04,593
Well, Mildred dear,
I wanted to tell you...

420
00:38:04,760 --> 00:38:07,194
- Her name is Lyudmila!
- Hush.

421
00:38:07,360 --> 00:38:09,590
My name is Margarita Pavlovna,

422
00:38:09,760 --> 00:38:13,912
not long ago I was his wife.

423
00:38:14,200 --> 00:38:17,988
We stopped being man and woman,
but we're still one family.

424
00:38:18,280 --> 00:38:24,435
That's why I take his life
close to my heart.

425
00:38:24,600 --> 00:38:28,593
- Please!
- But that is not the point.

426
00:38:29,200 --> 00:38:33,910
You see, Lev Evghenievich
is a bit of a character.

427
00:38:34,080 --> 00:38:36,833
He just can't concentrate.

428
00:38:37,000 --> 00:38:40,993
He had invited you, knowing very
well we'd have guests in the evening.

429
00:38:41,520 --> 00:38:43,590
Of course, I shall leave now.

430
00:38:44,520 --> 00:38:45,839
Lyudochka!

431
00:38:48,200 --> 00:38:50,350
You're so absent-minded!

432
00:38:50,520 --> 00:38:52,590
Good bye, Mildred!

433
00:38:55,280 --> 00:38:57,999
Mildred! Ah, Lyudochka!

434
00:39:09,920 --> 00:39:15,517
- This is outrageous!
- Khobotov, don't be ridiculous!

435
00:39:16,360 --> 00:39:19,989
Why ridiculous?
Say, I fell in love with someone!

436
00:39:20,200 --> 00:39:24,432
You can't fall in love, you,
a subconscious erotomaniac!

437
00:39:24,600 --> 00:39:30,596
If you meet someone
to arouse my confidence,

438
00:39:30,760 --> 00:39:34,514
someone to whom I could
entrust you, I'll be only happy.

439
00:39:34,680 --> 00:39:37,353
Get up. Come on.

440
00:39:37,520 --> 00:39:41,752
It's not polite to our guests.
Come on.

441
00:39:43,200 --> 00:39:45,839
There is no need
for somebody to think

442
00:39:46,000 --> 00:39:50,437
that our family undergoes some
petty cataclysms.

443
00:39:56,280 --> 00:39:58,430
Ah, Leva!

444
00:40:44,760 --> 00:40:46,990
All burins are different.

445
00:40:47,200 --> 00:40:51,671
There is a chisel,
and there is an etching needle.

446
00:40:51,920 --> 00:40:55,993
I must admit, there is
some ginger in him.

447
00:40:56,200 --> 00:40:59,829
For relief work only
a graver is used.

448
00:41:00,000 --> 00:41:02,673
- He's a real fanatic of his trade.
- Achtung!

449
00:41:02,840 --> 00:41:06,833
I engraved the champion's names
on the cups!

450
00:41:07,000 --> 00:41:12,597
Engraving other people's names
is an act of self-abnegation.

451
00:41:13,280 --> 00:41:16,272
- Khobotov, it's decadence.
- It's life.

452
00:41:16,760 --> 00:41:19,194
Some people win cups,

453
00:41:19,360 --> 00:41:23,512
and others engrave their names.

454
00:41:23,840 --> 00:41:28,834
I don't know nothing about self-
abnegation, but it's a very rough work.

455
00:41:29,000 --> 00:41:31,833
It can be done with
an etching needle.

456
00:41:32,000 --> 00:41:36,551
- A healthy approach to the subject!
- Sophistry's not for craftsmen.

457
00:41:37,280 --> 00:41:41,193
- What about diggers in 'Hamlet'?
- They're simply hacks!

458
00:41:58,840 --> 00:42:00,592
Great!

459
00:42:00,760 --> 00:42:04,070
They threw one girl up the other day
and never caught her.

460
00:42:04,280 --> 00:42:07,590
She's on a sick leave now.
Suspended from competitions.

461
00:42:08,840 --> 00:42:10,831
The 'Labour Reserves' Club.

462
00:42:11,000 --> 00:42:15,437
Svetlana is a professional swimmer,
she swims on her back nicely!

463
00:42:24,200 --> 00:42:27,431
I have a real man
in my house at last.

464
00:42:27,600 --> 00:42:30,194
My Savva is such a darling,
I am very happy.

465
00:42:30,360 --> 00:42:33,193
A wonderful evening!
'twas so fascinating!

466
00:42:33,360 --> 00:42:36,272
- I wanted to tell you...
- It's all right, I understand.

467
00:42:38,840 --> 00:42:41,752
'twas so invigorating!
C'est magnifique!

468
00:42:43,840 --> 00:42:48,595
But mind, the scraper is what
levels out the burr!..

469
00:42:48,760 --> 00:42:51,991
- He is absolutely possessed!
- This makes him so charming.

470
00:42:52,200 --> 00:42:56,193
I can tell you what it
all boils down to...

471
00:42:56,360 --> 00:42:59,830
I can see, my dear colleague.
For God's sake!..

472
00:43:00,000 --> 00:43:04,994
Lev Evghenievich, hold on.
I just admire your attitude.

473
00:43:05,200 --> 00:43:09,193
- You rose to the occasion!
- What do you mean?

474
00:43:09,360 --> 00:43:12,352
- Well, 'meine Freunde'!
- Au revoir!

475
00:43:12,520 --> 00:43:15,592
- Auf Wiedersehen!
- Good bye. Au revoir!

476
00:43:15,760 --> 00:43:18,832
- Auf Wiedergucken!
- Your humble servant...

477
00:43:19,760 --> 00:43:22,194
Savva. Lev...

478
00:43:22,600 --> 00:43:27,196
Highly spiritual relations!

479
00:43:28,520 --> 00:43:31,751
Just all right,
for intelligent people!

480
00:43:40,360 --> 00:43:42,351
I am so tired.

481
00:43:47,840 --> 00:43:51,196
What was the idea of mounting
your hobby-horse?

482
00:43:52,200 --> 00:43:55,829
Using burins in metal-work,
Margarita Pavlovna:

483
00:43:56,000 --> 00:43:59,595
engraving is a very delicate matter.
Haste makes waste.

484
00:44:00,760 --> 00:44:03,274
And you were such a wet blanket.

485
00:44:03,440 --> 00:44:06,910
I'm sure that with that Mildred
you're more eloquent!

486
00:44:07,080 --> 00:44:13,189
She's Lyudmila! And don't
mention her name in vain!

487
00:44:13,360 --> 00:44:18,912
- Vouzette ridicule, mon ami.
- Don't mention her name in vain!

488
00:44:20,440 --> 00:44:23,512
Darling, you should take
a course of injections.

489
00:44:24,200 --> 00:44:26,191
Well, let's go to sleep.

490
00:44:27,600 --> 00:44:30,672
- I can hardly stand on my feet.
- I'll just smoke a cigarette.

491
00:44:32,360 --> 00:44:37,753
Savva, I'm in complete despair.

492
00:44:37,920 --> 00:44:41,993
Lev Evghenievich, take it easy.
Everything will settle down.

493
00:44:42,200 --> 00:44:46,193
We'll get married by spring,
we'll move to a new apartment.

494
00:44:46,360 --> 00:44:48,999
You'll be your own master here,
you'll enjoy yourself!

495
00:44:49,200 --> 00:44:52,192
Many a thing can happen
before spring.

496
00:44:52,360 --> 00:44:55,989
You must understand her too.
Bringing girls here. She feels hurt.

497
00:44:56,600 --> 00:45:00,991
I'm bringing no girls!
It's different, a delicate matter.

498
00:45:02,920 --> 00:45:07,516
You can't imagine what I've gone
through during this evening.

499
00:45:09,440 --> 00:45:12,830
It's awful!

500
00:45:13,000 --> 00:45:15,992
Just calm down. You'll have
to be patient...

501
00:45:16,200 --> 00:45:19,192
- It's life.
- I understand.

502
00:45:19,360 --> 00:45:23,353
- It's nothing compared with war.
- I understand.

503
00:45:23,840 --> 00:45:25,432
Savva Ignatievich!..

504
00:45:45,680 --> 00:45:51,676
'Like a river you flow,
With a tender fairy-name,

505
00:45:53,200 --> 00:45:58,194
'And your pavement transparent -
Like in water-ways.

506
00:45:59,520 --> 00:46:05,595
'Ah, Arbat, my dear street,
You're my big destiny:

507
00:46:06,440 --> 00:46:11,912
'Therein lies my grief
And my happy days.

508
00:46:13,200 --> 00:46:18,354
'Ah, Arbat, my dear street.
You're my big destiny:

509
00:46:19,520 --> 00:46:24,833
'Therein lies my grief
And my happy days.

510
00:46:28,000 --> 00:46:33,996
'Passers-by walking you
Are simple-hearted legion.

511
00:46:35,000 --> 00:46:40,199
'The staccato of steps,
It's a busy day...

512
00:46:42,000 --> 00:46:47,518
'Ah, Arbat, my dear street,
You're my big religion.

513
00:46:48,440 --> 00:46:53,594
With your pavements beneath,
Here so nice to stay...

514
00:46:54,600 --> 00:47:00,197
'Ah, Arbat, my dear street,
You're my big religion.

515
00:47:00,920 --> 00:47:06,199
'With your pavements beneath,
Here so nice to stay...

516
00:47:09,000 --> 00:47:15,189
'I'm obsessed with this love,
Pavements sing a dear song.

517
00:47:16,000 --> 00:47:20,915
'Many streets that I knew
Were just foreign land.

518
00:47:22,200 --> 00:47:28,514
'Ah, Arbat, dear Arbat:
This is where I belong.

519
00:47:29,440 --> 00:47:34,195
'Walking you, walking you... -
You will never end.

520
00:47:35,600 --> 00:47:40,993
'Ah, Arbat, dear Arbat:
This is where I belong.

521
00:47:43,840 --> 00:47:46,991
'Walking you, walking you... -

522
00:47:49,000 --> 00:47:52,834
'You will never end...'

523
00:47:55,600 --> 00:48:01,835
My dear aquarium enwrapped
in sleep. Yes...

524
00:48:17,280 --> 00:48:20,590
'Hi, my audience, you at last!
Listen to my funny rhymes:

525
00:48:20,760 --> 00:48:23,433
'How some characters of past
Came to live in modern times...

526
00:48:27,080 --> 00:48:30,356
'Dame of Spades, a hapless lot,
Kicked the bucket on the spot.

527
00:48:30,520 --> 00:48:33,080
'Poor lady couldn't wait:
Ambulance a bit too late...

528
00:48:37,000 --> 00:48:40,515
'Romeo fancied: it would be good
To buy for Juliet some fast food.

529
00:48:40,680 --> 00:48:44,195
'Each of them a cutlet ate... -
Poor Romeo and Juliet!

530
00:48:48,600 --> 00:48:53,435
'My dear friend, don't knit your brow:
I'm a comedian, you know.

531
00:48:53,600 --> 00:48:57,991
'Is it satire? Not so much.
But I admit - there is some touch.

532
00:48:58,200 --> 00:49:02,990
'I'd like to mention therefore
A poet Nekrasov of the past:

533
00:49:03,200 --> 00:49:08,832
'You needn't be a poet, bro,
But civil spirit is a must!..'

534
00:50:02,920 --> 00:50:06,595
I have it, Margarita Pavlovna!
Here you are!

535
00:50:39,080 --> 00:50:41,913
Happy New Year, Alice.

536
00:50:42,440 --> 00:50:45,750
Happy New Year, Aziz.
May you be happy!

537
00:50:49,200 --> 00:50:52,192
The hendecassylabic metre
of the poet Thaletes

538
00:50:53,200 --> 00:50:57,830
is a complicated pentameter,

539
00:50:58,840 --> 00:51:01,991
consisting of four trochees

540
00:51:02,840 --> 00:51:05,195
and one dactyl,

541
00:51:05,360 --> 00:51:09,194
which took the second place.

542
00:51:10,360 --> 00:51:14,876
In classic prosody, namely

543
00:51:15,040 --> 00:51:18,032
in the hendecassylabic metre

544
00:51:19,200 --> 00:51:21,998
we meet a caesura, every time -

545
00:51:22,760 --> 00:51:25,752
after an arsis in the third foot.

546
00:51:27,000 --> 00:51:31,198
This prosody is quite adaptable
in Russian language too...

547
00:51:33,000 --> 00:51:37,357
- Please, Nina Andreevna.
- Thank you.

548
00:51:44,080 --> 00:51:48,437
'Like a ship all too eager
to neglect its rigging:

549
00:51:49,280 --> 00:51:53,068
'Now its sails billowing,
then - its oars feathering...

550
00:51:54,080 --> 00:51:57,595
'Likewise you: it's a double passion
that you seek...

551
00:51:57,840 --> 00:52:00,912
'You lad, seeking love...'

552
00:52:02,440 --> 00:52:04,670
- Jesus, I can't...
- '...Burning with passion...'

553
00:52:05,520 --> 00:52:09,911
'You lad, seeking love,
Burning with passion.

554
00:52:11,000 --> 00:52:14,913
'So do you, lass: bereft of love,
Shedding bitter tears,

555
00:52:15,440 --> 00:52:20,514
'You accept someone's
Unwelcome caresses...'

556
00:52:22,600 --> 00:52:27,993
'The snow whirling: a lovely scene!
The blue lights shimmering above:

557
00:52:28,200 --> 00:52:33,593
'Skating-rink gives a 'ring-ring'...
And reminds me of school-time love.

558
00:52:34,360 --> 00:52:40,196
'You're merging with lights, so near:
I'm calling and after you run...

559
00:52:42,360 --> 00:52:47,753
'Hey, catch me, I can hear.
You're playing with me. What a fun!

560
00:52:48,920 --> 00:52:53,596
'Hey, catch me, I can hear.
You're playing with me. What a fun!'

561
00:52:54,200 --> 00:52:56,839
'Falling snow, and
falling in love...

562
00:53:02,840 --> 00:53:06,913
Lev Evghenievich, poor thing!
Let me help you.

563
00:53:07,520 --> 00:53:09,351
Get up, my poor darling.

564
00:53:12,600 --> 00:53:17,196
- It's all my blame.
- No, I'm too clumsy.

565
00:53:17,360 --> 00:53:20,989
No, you skate nicely!

566
00:53:23,000 --> 00:53:24,991
Are you hurt that much?

567
00:53:25,200 --> 00:53:28,749
I just remembered about
Bertrand Dufois.

568
00:53:28,920 --> 00:53:31,753
- Who was he?
- A trouvere of things hedonic.

569
00:53:31,920 --> 00:53:34,832
- What happened to him?
- He fell down and died.

570
00:53:35,000 --> 00:53:36,592
How awful!

571
00:53:37,200 --> 00:53:39,839
You should be administered
an anti-tetanus serum!

572
00:53:40,000 --> 00:53:44,198
You, an educated person, you
can't see elementary things!

573
00:53:44,360 --> 00:53:46,351
You saw what happened with
that trouver of yours?..

574
00:53:46,520 --> 00:53:48,351
Ah, Kostya!

575
00:53:49,520 --> 00:53:52,751
- What happened with you?
- Just hurt myself a bit.

576
00:53:52,920 --> 00:53:57,198
- He made a turn and fell down.
- It's a usual thing.

577
00:53:57,360 --> 00:54:00,352
Girls, go and skate a bit,
I'll sit and talk with Lev Evghenievich.

578
00:54:00,520 --> 00:54:03,830
- You will not leave him?
- Of course not!

579
00:54:04,000 --> 00:54:07,993
What the hell you are doing here?

580
00:54:08,200 --> 00:54:12,512
Margarita didn't accept her,
so - I'm 'spinning' here.

581
00:54:13,200 --> 00:54:16,351
In my age, living some
illusory life...

582
00:54:16,520 --> 00:54:19,193
We go to the flicks,
the last seances.

583
00:54:19,360 --> 00:54:22,352
We were at the operetta.
Now - at the skating rink...

584
00:54:22,520 --> 00:54:25,990
We also were at a lecture. She was
so kind to take the challenge...

585
00:54:26,200 --> 00:54:30,591
- So, she is a kind girl, isn't she?
- Very kind. And very emotional too.

586
00:54:30,760 --> 00:54:34,389
I told her about Francois Villon -
she nearly sobbed for pity.

587
00:54:34,560 --> 00:54:37,597
Wow, I guess he was stabbed or
hanged up or something like that.

588
00:54:38,200 --> 00:54:40,998
He died under strange circumstances.

589
00:54:41,360 --> 00:54:43,590
You will scare the girl

590
00:54:45,440 --> 00:54:47,510
out of her wits, Lev Evghenievich.

591
00:54:47,920 --> 00:54:53,756
What do you think: can I expect
that my love be reciprocated?

592
00:54:54,280 --> 00:54:57,352
You? By Jove, of course!

593
00:54:57,520 --> 00:55:01,069
You're the incarnate virtue!
Life is great, Lev Evghenievich!

594
00:55:02,440 --> 00:55:05,750
Kostya, what shall I do now?
I fell in love with her!

595
00:55:06,000 --> 00:55:10,198
You must mold your own life,
be a master of your destiny.

596
00:55:31,440 --> 00:55:34,079
- It's she!
- Who?! Margarita Pavlovna?

597
00:55:34,600 --> 00:55:38,195
No, it's she. Stay here,
I'll be back in a moment...

598
00:55:54,000 --> 00:55:57,993
Lev Evghenievich! Poor thing,
he left you alone?

599
00:55:59,000 --> 00:56:00,831
I was waiting for you.

600
00:56:01,000 --> 00:56:03,594
Shall we go? I shall see you home.

601
00:56:03,760 --> 00:56:07,355
- No, I love it being here.
- Oh really?

602
00:56:07,920 --> 00:56:12,835
Yes, these lights,
this marvelous spinning.

603
00:56:15,600 --> 00:56:19,593
You in this lovely sweater,
and this music...

604
00:56:19,760 --> 00:56:22,752
And I loved that polka dance
so much!

605
00:56:41,760 --> 00:56:43,990
I could hardly find you.

606
00:56:44,600 --> 00:56:47,194
- Why're you looking for me?
- I was told to.

607
00:56:47,600 --> 00:56:49,352
- Hi.
- Good evening.

608
00:56:49,520 --> 00:56:53,069
The boy living next door said he
saw you here, on the Clear Pond.

609
00:56:53,280 --> 00:56:55,748
What business did he have
telling on me!

610
00:56:55,920 --> 00:57:00,277
He is just a kid, you can't blame him.
Margarita threw herself into a tantrum!

611
00:57:00,680 --> 00:57:02,671
She asked me to bring you home.

612
00:57:02,840 --> 00:57:05,593
For God's sake!
Savva, go home.

613
00:57:05,760 --> 00:57:09,912
- Don't get into a huff.
- Yes, I'll see you home...

614
00:57:10,080 --> 00:57:12,594
Either you leave now, or
everything is over between us!

615
00:57:12,760 --> 00:57:14,830
Wow!

616
00:57:15,000 --> 00:57:16,991
Lyuda, let's go on skating.

617
00:57:22,760 --> 00:57:25,672
- Savva, you here too?
- Kostya...

618
00:57:26,080 --> 00:57:28,514
- Where is Lev Evghenievich?
- He's skating.

619
00:57:28,680 --> 00:57:33,674
Margarita can't find any peace
without him, and he's skating!

620
00:57:37,840 --> 00:57:41,515
- What do they want from him?
- They care for his fragile life.

621
00:57:41,680 --> 00:57:44,990
- The ice is slippery.
- You slip, you take a risk.

622
00:57:45,200 --> 00:57:48,192
Right you are,
you've said a mouthful.

623
00:57:49,200 --> 00:57:52,192
I've received yet another wire
from Velyurov.

624
00:57:52,440 --> 00:57:54,431
He'll go bankrupt, really.

625
00:57:54,600 --> 00:57:56,431
- Don't tease me.
- I'm being serious.

626
00:57:56,760 --> 00:58:01,436
By the way, he is
a very nice person.

627
00:58:01,600 --> 00:58:05,434
Oh yeah, all the war hawks
look at him with trepidation.

628
00:58:05,600 --> 00:58:08,194
- What about you?
- I'm a person of free choice.

629
00:58:08,600 --> 00:58:12,434
- And there he is, by the way.
- Wow! And he too!

630
00:58:13,360 --> 00:58:15,351
He looks quite imposing!

631
00:58:15,520 --> 00:58:19,832
I'll split. I don't want
to upset him without need.

632
00:58:20,520 --> 00:58:23,751
God will reward you
for your kindness.

633
00:58:31,920 --> 00:58:34,912
Why are you wandering here,
oh restless soul?

634
00:58:35,080 --> 00:58:39,835
I feel so blue, I need
to get distracted.

635
00:58:40,000 --> 00:58:42,833
- What depresses you so?
- You wouldn't understand.

636
00:58:43,000 --> 00:58:47,676
- You're having a crisis?
- Like any artiste, I do.

637
00:58:47,840 --> 00:58:50,832
You've just outgrown
stand-up comedy.

638
00:58:51,000 --> 00:58:53,992
You can't play one and
the same role all your life.

639
00:58:54,200 --> 00:58:58,432
An artiste must be in constant
search and don different clothes.

640
00:58:58,600 --> 00:59:02,593
- Your dinner-jacket is not popular.
- I'm a master of the word!

641
00:59:02,760 --> 00:59:04,990
No, a writer is.

642
00:59:05,520 --> 00:59:09,593
I'm a reciter, a soloist,
a master of skits and lampoons!

643
00:59:09,760 --> 00:59:13,355
You can't depend on Soev and
his spouse all your life.

644
00:59:13,520 --> 00:59:17,513
- An artiste must change his outfit!
- You're so emphatically monosyllabic!

645
00:59:17,680 --> 00:59:19,989
Well, it's up to you, Velyurov.

646
00:59:20,200 --> 00:59:22,509
- You feel bad?
- Can you see...

647
00:59:24,200 --> 00:59:27,431
- What? Whom?
- It's she!

648
00:59:27,600 --> 00:59:30,512
- Who?
- Oh, what a beauty!

649
01:00:24,200 --> 01:00:29,433
She disappeared.
A glimpse, a vision, a mirage...

650
01:00:30,360 --> 01:00:33,830
A vision, a mirage...
It's in the spirit of the day.

651
01:00:35,600 --> 01:00:38,592
But there is a hope I'll find her!

652
01:00:56,920 --> 01:00:59,912
Lyuda, it's me.
I've good news for you!

653
01:01:00,080 --> 01:01:03,197
Excuse me.
Lyuda, I've got good news!

654
01:01:04,440 --> 01:01:07,432
They're getting married tomorrow!

655
01:01:08,520 --> 01:01:10,750
At 13 p.m, yes.

656
01:01:10,920 --> 01:01:15,198
At this hour we'll be admiring
the Novodevichy monastery frescoes.

657
01:01:15,360 --> 01:01:19,672
No, nothing is wrong with my
breathing, no asthma!

658
01:01:19,840 --> 01:01:23,435
I'm healthy! I'm happy!
I love you, Lyudochka!

659
01:01:23,600 --> 01:01:25,670
I kiss you!

660
01:01:28,200 --> 01:01:31,829
What's wrong with you?
Why're you wearing a fur-coat?

661
01:01:32,760 --> 01:01:37,197
It's awfully cold. I'm awfully cold.

662
01:01:39,600 --> 01:01:41,591
I'm cold...

