Hey, good people, listen!

683
01:03:08,880 --> 01:03:12,953
'We'll give you a lot of fun,
We'll keep the tradition!

684
01:03:13,120 --> 01:03:17,432
'Jesters with a funny face,
For the crowd to jeer:

685
01:03:17,640 --> 01:03:21,349
'Circus now a marketplace,
You can buy things here!'

686
01:03:22,640 --> 01:03:26,633
Well, I've bought everything.
Where is Arkady?

687
01:03:27,880 --> 01:03:32,032
We shouldn't have entrusted
him with strong drinks.

688
01:03:32,200 --> 01:03:35,636
Arkady, Margarita told us
not to be too long.

689
01:03:35,800 --> 01:03:38,439
- Take it easy.
- Arkady, alles gemacht!

690
01:03:38,640 --> 01:03:41,438
Funf Minuten', Savva Ignatievich.

691
01:03:42,040 --> 01:03:43,951
'Hey, come hither!

692
01:03:44,120 --> 01:03:49,194
'Many barkers in the town,
But the best one is a clown.

693
01:03:49,360 --> 01:03:55,037
'Buy a ticket, Muscovite,
We're all too glad to sell!

694
01:03:55,440 --> 01:04:01,629
'We the gates shall open wide,
We shall ring the bell!'

695
01:04:11,520 --> 01:04:16,640
Once I met a woman
of extraordinary beauty.

696
01:04:16,800 --> 01:04:20,873
For the one getting married these
are quite inappropriate recollections.

697
01:04:21,040 --> 01:04:22,632
I've no ulterior motive.

698
01:04:22,800 --> 01:04:26,873
He is turning over a leaf,
let him give vent to his feelings.

699
01:04:27,040 --> 01:04:30,032
As bride's witness, you
didn't rise to the occasion.

700
01:04:30,200 --> 01:04:33,192
You are a moralist,
and it is unbearable.

701
01:04:33,360 --> 01:04:36,193
- Yep, I am a moralist!
- You are a Pharisee!

702
01:04:39,640 --> 01:04:42,632
- Where were you last night?
- I had a simultaneous chess game.

703
01:04:42,800 --> 01:04:44,791
A simultaneous love game maybe?

704
01:04:44,960 --> 01:04:50,796
- I'm 10 min from being a grandmaster!
- You are already a master!

705
01:04:51,040 --> 01:04:53,429
Oh, let us be going now.

706
01:04:55,120 --> 01:04:57,111
Alice, it is for Kostya.

707
01:04:57,280 --> 01:05:01,034
- Let them call a bit later.
- All right.

708
01:05:01,200 --> 01:05:03,509
Would you call a bit later?

709
01:05:06,040 --> 01:05:10,431
- Arkady, let's be going.
- Let go of me.

710
01:05:10,640 --> 01:05:16,272
- Really, we must go now.
- I'm feeling blue like the poet Blok.

711
01:05:16,440 --> 01:05:17,714
What?

712
01:05:17,880 --> 01:05:20,189
- My naiad has disappeared.
- Don't panic.

713
01:05:20,360 --> 01:05:22,715
I have showered her with telegrams.

714
01:05:22,880 --> 01:05:26,429
Too bad. I could open your eyes
on a lot of things.

715
01:05:26,640 --> 01:05:30,792
You should be more up-to-date,
keep in tune with reality.

716
01:05:30,960 --> 01:05:35,192
- The end of the century is in the air.
- What do you mean?

717
01:05:35,360 --> 01:05:38,272
You're calling her a naiad, speaking
about feeling blue like Blok.

718
01:05:38,440 --> 01:05:41,273
- And you're three sheets in the wind.
- Kostya, don't be rude.

719
01:05:41,440 --> 01:05:46,434
- A naiad! She is a swimmer!
- Call her Madama Butterfly.

720
01:05:46,640 --> 01:05:50,269
There is such a swimming stroke,
a very progressive one.

721
01:05:50,440 --> 01:05:53,034
- No kidding?
- Not at all, I know it.

722
01:05:53,200 --> 01:05:55,430
I need to think about it. A cafe!
I'll catch up with you.

723
01:05:55,640 --> 01:05:58,712
- We are going together now!
- Oh no!

724
01:05:58,960 --> 01:06:01,952
Kostya? He'll be any minute now.

725
01:06:02,120 --> 01:06:06,432
Yes, I'll put it down,
I'll just take a pencil.

726
01:06:07,520 --> 01:06:09,351
Ah, here he is.

727
01:06:11,040 --> 01:06:14,510
Yes? Oh, what a surprise!

728
01:06:14,720 --> 01:06:18,349
Your boyfriend in the army now?..

729
01:06:18,520 --> 01:06:21,637
Ah, I see. Right. Bye.

730
01:06:21,800 --> 01:06:24,030
Compexes, complexes...

731
01:06:27,120 --> 01:06:28,633
A butterfly!

732
01:06:28,800 --> 01:06:33,032
- You're plastered!
- What a hail-fellow manner!

733
01:06:33,200 --> 01:06:36,033
I know my limit all too well.

734
01:06:36,200 --> 01:06:40,637
But as for you... I've been observing
you for quite a long time.

735
01:06:40,800 --> 01:06:45,794
I remember how you talked with
Sveta and how you stared at her!

736
01:06:45,960 --> 01:06:50,795
- What do you mean?
- You... you!..

737
01:06:52,280 --> 01:06:54,271
You were craving her!

738
01:06:54,440 --> 01:06:59,275
- What a cheek! It's slander!
- I know what' I'm talking about!

739
01:06:59,440 --> 01:07:02,716
- You can blow the wedding!
- Nonsense!

740
01:07:04,040 --> 01:07:08,033
- You're the bride's witness.
- I can control myself!

741
01:07:08,800 --> 01:07:12,952
- Sveta has walked out on me!
- Look at your humble servant:

742
01:07:13,120 --> 01:07:18,035
in a wink I met and then
lost a girl of my dream.

743
01:07:18,200 --> 01:07:21,112
And what do you think? I passed
my exams yesterday, all right?

744
01:07:21,280 --> 01:07:24,636
There is someone... Oh Jesus...

745
01:07:24,800 --> 01:07:27,439
There is someone
between the two of us.

746
01:07:27,640 --> 01:07:31,189
The young lot, especially the fair one,
are too undemanding nowadays.

747
01:07:31,360 --> 01:07:35,433
But she was at my concert,
she witnessed my success!

748
01:07:35,640 --> 01:07:38,438
You shouldn't bemoan it:
she fell short.

749
01:07:38,640 --> 01:07:41,950
- You think so?
- She is a flippant girl.

750
01:07:42,120 --> 01:07:44,395
The Festival of Youth is at hand.

751
01:07:44,560 --> 01:07:46,630
There will come handsome guys
from New Zealand!..

752
01:07:46,800 --> 01:07:49,872
If you let feelings take the most
of you, you would pine away!

753
01:07:50,040 --> 01:07:52,713
- It makes sense.
- So, you are lucky then!

754
01:07:52,880 --> 01:07:57,271
- After all, I'm Velyurov!
- Right you are.

755
01:07:57,440 --> 01:07:59,795
- I'm Velyurov!
- Velyurov indeed!

756
01:07:59,960 --> 01:08:03,032
- I'm Velyurov!
- You've said a mouthful!

757
01:08:04,120 --> 01:08:06,111
Arkady Varlamovich, excuse me.

758
01:08:07,200 --> 01:08:09,191
Anna Adamovna!

759
01:08:13,040 --> 01:08:14,871
Hi.

760
01:08:15,200 --> 01:08:18,192
- Why are you so late?
- I don't know myself.

761
01:08:22,040 --> 01:08:24,873
- I'm having a wedding today.
- How come?

762
01:08:25,040 --> 01:08:27,634
I'm the bridegroom's best man.

763
01:08:27,800 --> 01:08:32,032
- Please meet the bridesmaid.
- How do you do.

764
01:08:33,120 --> 01:08:36,635
Ah, I'm at a loss, you know.
I was thinking, thinking...

765
01:08:38,280 --> 01:08:41,033
Shall I drop in or shall I not...

766
01:08:43,120 --> 01:08:46,192
- I've dropped in just for a minute.
- Yes, of course.

767
01:08:46,360 --> 01:08:48,430
The books are waiting for you.

768
01:08:49,440 --> 01:08:53,638
I'm so absurd, you know,
so faltering.

769
01:08:54,640 --> 01:08:58,030
So illogical!..

770
01:09:09,800 --> 01:09:11,358
Yes? Yes?

771
01:09:11,720 --> 01:09:14,188
- Hi.
- What is it, Margo?

772
01:09:14,360 --> 01:09:16,874
- How is your side feeling?
- It hurts a bit.

773
01:09:17,040 --> 01:09:21,352
- I'm sorry, it's such a mess here.
- It's all right. Are you alone?

774
01:09:21,520 --> 01:09:24,717
Yes, though I can't understand
how it may concern you.

775
01:09:25,040 --> 01:09:29,636
- And what about the skating rink?
- What about it?

776
01:09:29,800 --> 01:09:33,031
You're very secretive. We've
been together for 15 years,

777
01:09:33,200 --> 01:09:36,272
and it never occurred to me
you were a skating star!

778
01:09:36,640 --> 01:09:39,632
People change, given
certain circumstances.

779
01:09:40,640 --> 01:09:43,871
That injure will tell
on your appendix.

780
01:09:44,960 --> 01:09:47,633
- You're going somewhere?
- Yes.

781
01:09:47,800 --> 01:09:50,109
- Alone?
- It's none of your business.

782
01:09:50,280 --> 01:09:56,276
It's not your self speaking,
it's your vacuum crying out!

783
01:09:56,440 --> 01:10:02,276
The vacuum which you strive
to fill artificially!

784
01:10:02,440 --> 01:10:06,956
- You have no need of her!
- You are no judge!

785
01:10:07,120 --> 01:10:11,033
I know better what you need.
I saw that small forehead of hers...

786
01:10:11,200 --> 01:10:13,430
Would you be so kind
as to show some respect!

787
01:10:13,640 --> 01:10:17,428
You just taking revenge on me!

788
01:10:17,640 --> 01:10:21,792
Some silly commonplace,
a shame to any thinking man!

789
01:10:21,960 --> 01:10:25,635
I'm not asking you whether you're
going alone to the wedding ceremony!

790
01:10:25,800 --> 01:10:28,633
- You're suffering!
- I don't want your sympathy!

791
01:10:28,800 --> 01:10:31,792
You must pay Savva his dues.
You know he's a virtuous man.

792
01:10:31,960 --> 01:10:36,431
- Things prosper in his hands.
- Things burn down in yours!

793
01:10:36,640 --> 01:10:41,634
I've been spoiling your life.
Now we're free, the two of us!

794
01:10:42,440 --> 01:10:45,876
You think now you can
demonstrate your inclinations?

795
01:10:46,040 --> 01:10:48,031
- What inclinations?
- I remember everything.

796
01:10:48,200 --> 01:10:51,431
How you came home late,
which, being not too circumspect,

797
01:10:51,640 --> 01:10:55,030
you explained by that usual
absentmindedness of yours!

798
01:10:55,200 --> 01:10:58,431
- Or how you didn't come to dacha!
- I lost my key!

799
01:10:58,640 --> 01:11:04,237
Or that harlot from the Scandinavian
office, with that sinful mouth of hers!

800
01:11:04,400 --> 01:11:07,631
Excuse me, I can't proceed
back-talking like this!

801
01:11:07,800 --> 01:11:12,874
- May you and Savva be happy.
- You must be back home at 3 p.m.

802
01:11:21,440 --> 01:11:26,434
Darling, you're so excited!
This is a once-in-a-lifetime day!

803
01:11:26,640 --> 01:11:28,790
May I remind you,
I was married before.

804
01:11:30,440 --> 01:11:34,035
When you read all these books,

805
01:11:35,640 --> 01:11:39,349
a truth will open up before you:
abstention,

806
01:11:40,040 --> 01:11:41,268
abstention,

807
01:11:43,920 --> 01:11:45,433
abstention!..

808
01:11:46,440 --> 01:11:47,953
I don't know really.

809
01:11:49,960 --> 01:11:53,350
I am so sudden,

810
01:11:54,200 --> 01:11:57,431
so illogical...

811
01:12:01,960 --> 01:12:04,190
Kostya! The taxi is here!

812
01:12:04,640 --> 01:12:08,872
Margarita, Savva! Your wedding
'carriage' is at the doors!

813
01:12:12,120 --> 01:12:15,430
- But where is your veil?
- Stop it, Kostya!

814
01:12:15,640 --> 01:12:18,632
- Savva, you're magnificent!
- Well...

815
01:12:18,800 --> 01:12:22,634
- And where is Arkady?
- Arkady, it's time to go!

816
01:12:26,960 --> 01:12:28,279
Arkady Varlamovich.

817
01:12:28,640 --> 01:12:30,870
- What does that mean?
- I'm just reclining.

818
01:12:31,040 --> 01:12:33,634
- You must be crazy!
- I'm not feeling well.

819
01:12:33,800 --> 01:12:37,031
- This is outrageous!
- Have you no sense of duty?

820
01:12:37,200 --> 01:12:40,431
I have. But I can't.

821
01:12:41,120 --> 01:12:44,635
- Arkady Varlamovich!
- No!

822
01:12:44,800 --> 01:12:49,032
He can't stand witness: he'll turn
the wedding prayer into a farce!

823
01:12:49,320 --> 01:12:53,029
- We're being late. What do we do?
- We need another witness.

824
01:12:55,640 --> 01:12:58,791
Lev, Arkady is out of order.
You'll stand witness.

825
01:12:58,960 --> 01:13:02,794
- But I can't!
- No way out. Hold on.

826
01:13:02,960 --> 01:13:05,952
- Hold on, Levushka.
- Let Alice do this for you.

827
01:13:06,120 --> 01:13:09,157
My dear friend, I'm cooking! I'm
the chef of the wedding table!

828
01:13:09,960 --> 01:13:12,633
- Lev, help us out!
- We'll tell you what to do.

829
01:13:13,040 --> 01:13:17,636
I'm having a date! We're going
to watch the frescoes!

830
01:13:17,800 --> 01:13:21,952
- You must offer this sacrifice.
- We'll go in a taxi.

831
01:13:22,120 --> 01:13:25,635
You're a knight without fear
and without reproach!

832
01:13:26,040 --> 01:13:29,350
- We'll go in a taxi!
- Some Stone Age!

833
01:13:30,640 --> 01:13:32,631
God's speed to you!..

834
01:13:34,640 --> 01:13:37,632
It'll take just a moment, Lev.
Setzen Sie bitte.

835
01:13:38,120 --> 01:13:41,635
- It's outrageous!
- Lev, don't be detrimental.

836
01:13:42,040 --> 01:13:43,439
Svetlana!..

837
01:13:44,520 --> 01:13:46,636
Svetlana!..

838
01:13:48,440 --> 01:13:51,034
Hush, you shameless type!

839
01:13:59,120 --> 01:14:02,112
Lev, everything will be all right.

840
01:14:04,880 --> 01:14:07,440
What frescoes was he talking about?

841
01:14:07,640 --> 01:14:11,269
Lev Evghenievich was going to visit
the Novodevichy Monastery.

842
01:14:11,440 --> 01:14:12,793
It's crazy!

843
01:14:12,960 --> 01:14:16,873
There's a fine touch: you getting
married, he going to the monastery!

844
01:14:32,800 --> 01:14:37,271
Lev Evghenievich, look
who is sitting at the table...

845
01:14:37,440 --> 01:14:41,115
- Poor thing, waiting for me there.
- Jesus, here you go again...

846
01:14:41,640 --> 01:14:44,791
Savva, just take
a look at this girl.

847
01:14:44,960 --> 01:14:48,794
- She is pretty!
- No, she is magnificent!

848
01:14:48,960 --> 01:14:52,635
Savva Ignatievich is on quite
different business here.

849
01:14:52,800 --> 01:14:55,109
Oh yes, I beg your pardon.

850
01:14:55,960 --> 01:15:00,715
Excuse me, do you haunt the skating
rink at the Clear Pond?

851
01:15:00,880 --> 01:15:03,314
- Not too often, but I do.
- I saw you there, for sure.

852
01:15:03,480 --> 01:15:07,439
- Kostya, for God's sake...
- One moment, Lev Evghenievich.

853
01:15:07,640 --> 01:15:11,428
What do you feel for those going
through the wedding ceremony:

854
01:15:11,640 --> 01:15:15,633
Resentment, sympathy, or maybe -
the motherly love?

855
01:15:15,800 --> 01:15:19,270
When you're going to get married,
I'll tell you. Are you a reporter?

856
01:15:19,440 --> 01:15:25,037
I'm a historian, but modern days
arouse my quick interest.

857
01:15:26,680 --> 01:15:28,671
- What is your name?
- Rita.

858
01:15:28,840 --> 01:15:31,115
- What?
- Margarita.

859
01:15:33,440 --> 01:15:39,436
- You are the would-be husband?
- No, but I'm the potential one.

860
01:15:41,960 --> 01:15:44,428
- So, it's you then?
- No, it's not me.

861
01:15:44,640 --> 01:15:48,633
- Aren't you getting married?
- It's quite the other way round.

862
01:15:48,800 --> 01:15:52,110
Savva, Ignatievich, will you
please step forward.

863
01:15:52,440 --> 01:15:54,032
Ein Moment.

864
01:15:56,280 --> 01:15:58,111
Margarita...

865
01:15:59,040 --> 01:16:03,636
Margarita, do you take this man
Savva to be your husband?

866
01:16:03,800 --> 01:16:05,438
Naturally.

867
01:16:05,640 --> 01:16:09,030
Savva, do you take this woman
Margarita to be your wife?

868
01:16:09,200 --> 01:16:10,792
Naturlich.

869
01:16:11,360 --> 01:16:15,273
As a token of love and faithfulness -
exchange your rings.

870
01:16:20,200 --> 01:16:22,191
Now kiss each other.

871
01:16:24,520 --> 01:16:29,116
And put your signatures
here and here.

872
01:16:32,320 --> 01:16:35,312
- Now - the witnesses.
- Excuse me, I'm in a hurry.

873
01:16:37,040 --> 01:16:38,189
Khobotov!

874
01:16:38,360 --> 01:16:41,636
Witness, are you a relative
of this newlywed woman?

875
01:16:41,800 --> 01:16:45,634
Alas, from this moment on -
I am not, anymore.

876
01:16:45,800 --> 01:16:47,791
Khobotov, I appreciated everything.

877
01:16:48,960 --> 01:16:50,951
Your turn.

878
01:16:51,640 --> 01:16:53,631
- You and me.
- What?

879
01:16:53,800 --> 01:16:56,268
I mean, gimme your pen.

880
01:16:58,720 --> 01:17:02,030
Konstantin Romin:
don't forget my name.

881
01:17:02,520 --> 01:17:04,636
- I shall try to.
- Be sure and do this.

882
01:17:04,800 --> 01:17:09,271
Konstantin in the ancient
language means 'constant'.

883
01:17:09,960 --> 01:17:14,033
- Can I go now?
- Witness, have some patience.

884
01:17:15,280 --> 01:17:17,794
Margarita Pavlovna and
Savva Ignatievich:

885
01:17:17,960 --> 01:17:21,953
I pronounce you man and wife.

886
01:17:22,280 --> 01:17:25,511
And my congratulations.

887
01:17:26,880 --> 01:17:28,632
My congratulations.

888
01:17:31,800 --> 01:17:33,950
Now the music, please...

889
01:17:42,120 --> 01:17:46,432
'They're angels of love,
Tender sentinels: their beat

890
01:17:47,640 --> 01:17:52,430
'Is Pokrovsky Gates
and Neglinka Street.

891
01:17:53,800 --> 01:17:58,430
'All the length of Arbat
They're treading along:

892
01:18:00,440 --> 01:18:06,197
'Their shift is only life-long...

893
01:18:09,120 --> 01:18:13,432
'Oh how sweet their numerous army,

894
01:18:14,960 --> 01:18:18,794
'Only soldiers, no marshals above.

895
01:18:18,960 --> 01:18:23,795
'They know not the perdition of money,
Equal before commandment of Love.

896
01:18:26,800 --> 01:18:31,271
'Love eternal is their campaign

897
01:18:32,640 --> 01:18:36,633
'In the face of the snow-storm
and pain.

898
01:18:36,800 --> 01:18:42,352
'To such Army my praise I sing:
It's the seizure of Moscow by spring.

899
01:18:43,640 --> 01:18:48,430
'They're angels of love,
Tender sentinels, their beat

900
01:18:49,640 --> 01:18:54,270
'Is Pokrovsky Gates
and Volkhonka Street.

901
01:18:55,640 --> 01:19:00,111
'All the length of Arbat
They're treading along:

902
01:19:02,280 --> 01:19:09,630
'Their shift is only life-long...'

903
01:19:16,800 --> 01:19:20,873
Lyudochka! Sorry.
Kostya, it's for you.

904
01:19:21,640 --> 01:19:23,870
Lev Evghenievich, for God's sake!

905
01:19:24,640 --> 01:19:27,518
- He's feeling blue.
- Savva!

906
01:19:28,400 --> 01:19:30,960
Didn't I ask you to be quiet,
while I'm working with the author!

907
01:19:31,120 --> 01:19:32,269
I'm desperately sorry.

908
01:19:34,280 --> 01:19:36,794
Soev, let's give it another try.

909
01:19:40,040 --> 01:19:45,034
' 'twas war, what a joke I could tell:
Satire - a fire to burn.

910
01:19:45,200 --> 01:19:51,196
'It's peace in the air I can smell:
It means I shall make a U-turn.'

911
01:19:51,640 --> 01:19:56,430
With all due respect for Mrs Soev,
but is that a finale?

912
01:19:56,640 --> 01:19:59,438
- A brilliant finale!
- This - a finale?!.

913
01:19:59,640 --> 01:20:01,631
'It means I shall make a U-turn...'

914
01:20:01,800 --> 01:20:05,429
- A brilliant finale!
- It's your old variations!

915
01:20:05,640 --> 01:20:08,279
You're not a Shakespeare to do this.

916
01:20:08,440 --> 01:20:12,638
Shakespeare? You want me
to improvise? Very well...

917
01:20:15,680 --> 01:20:19,639
'Tucked under the bed was the war:
Leaned down I, and gave a start:

918
01:20:20,200 --> 01:20:24,352
'She was a tough lady not long before.
I nearly died, cross my heart!

919
01:20:24,960 --> 01:20:29,272
'A young coachman skirted the sea,
In the bushes he angled the herring!

920
01:20:29,960 --> 01:20:31,359
'Angled the herring!'

921
01:20:32,040 --> 01:20:34,031
Stop it!

922
01:20:35,440 --> 01:20:37,431
Oh, for God's sake!

923
01:20:38,960 --> 01:20:43,636
Yes. it's me. Your boyfriend
still in the army?

924
01:20:43,800 --> 01:20:46,439
But I am going away too, you know.

925
01:20:46,640 --> 01:20:50,030
They've found an ancient city
on the bottom of the lake Titicaca.

926
01:20:50,200 --> 01:20:54,955
I am going away for a very long time.
I'm crossing her out.

927
01:20:55,440 --> 01:20:57,635
It's not funny, you know.

928
01:20:57,800 --> 01:21:01,031
It doesn't matter now. I'm in
for a great change in my life.

929
01:21:04,040 --> 01:21:06,634
It's you. Good afternoon.

930
01:21:09,200 --> 01:21:12,192
- How did you like the film?
- A total lack of talent!

931
01:21:12,360 --> 01:21:15,636
Dear auntie, art still
owes you a nice film.

932
01:21:19,960 --> 01:21:21,951
Speaking of art...

933
01:21:26,800 --> 01:21:31,794
Sveta Popova! It's for you.

934
01:21:32,880 --> 01:21:34,871
- Hello?
- Hi.

935
01:21:35,040 --> 01:21:38,635
- Is that you, Kostya?
- Yes.

936
01:21:38,800 --> 01:21:41,792
- Something is wrong with you?
- Absolutely not.

937
01:21:41,960 --> 01:21:44,633
- I'm going away.
- Where to?

938
01:21:44,800 --> 01:21:47,951
The Black Earth region. They've found
the skull of the prophet Oleg's horsie.

939
01:21:48,120 --> 01:21:52,272
- I read about this in the papers.
- You're such a smart girl.

940
01:21:52,440 --> 01:21:57,195
By the by, Velyurov has prepared
an outstanding program!

941
01:21:57,360 --> 01:22:01,433
He'll be the hit of the
World Festival of Youth.

942
01:22:01,640 --> 01:22:05,269
Yes, he's my nice 'step-son'!

943
01:22:05,440 --> 01:22:06,634
Bye, Sveta.

944
01:22:06,800 --> 01:22:10,270
I wish you to win
all the gold medals!

945
01:22:10,440 --> 01:22:12,431
He must be crazy...

946
01:22:18,240 --> 01:22:20,629
We're in for great changes!

947
01:22:27,960 --> 01:22:30,030
Well, Savva...

948
01:22:33,040 --> 01:22:36,032
Check. Leonty, give a hand
to your fellow-in-arms.

949
01:22:36,800 --> 01:22:39,792
- Lev, make your move.
- Yes, of course.

950
01:22:53,720 --> 01:22:57,030
Hey, son, move your brains.

951
01:23:08,040 --> 01:23:11,874
Once a lady came to me.

952
01:23:13,040 --> 01:23:16,032
She wanted me to engrave
an inscription.

953
01:23:16,640 --> 01:23:18,870
- On what?
- On the wrist-watch.

954
01:23:20,040 --> 01:23:26,639
The inscription went like this:
'Thanks for the lovely seconds...'

955
01:23:27,880 --> 01:23:34,433
A present to an artiste? No, she said.
To a writer? - No.

956
01:23:34,640 --> 01:23:39,111
- To whom then?
- It was meant for her husband!

957
01:23:39,640 --> 01:23:44,111
For you as a newlywed this
is a nice story to tell.

958
01:23:44,640 --> 01:23:48,872
Savva, you promised to solder
a saucepan for me!

959
01:23:49,040 --> 01:23:51,634
Naturlich, Margarita Pavlovna.

960
01:23:52,640 --> 01:23:54,631
Check and mate, Savva!

961
01:23:58,200 --> 01:24:03,274
You were a first-rate engraver!
I am totally positive of that.

962
01:24:03,440 --> 01:24:07,877
We're going to the building site.
We'll be moving in any day now.

963
01:24:08,040 --> 01:24:09,439
That's great!

964
01:24:17,640 --> 01:24:22,634
My untiresome friend Savransky
knows some architect.

965
01:24:22,800 --> 01:24:27,112
He says they're going
to dismantle our humble castle.

966
01:24:27,360 --> 01:24:29,032
And where are we going then?

967
01:24:29,200 --> 01:24:32,192
Take it easy, Lev, the government
will take care of you.

968
01:24:32,440 --> 01:24:36,638
Oh yeah, you shaking dust from
your feet, leaving me here.

969
01:24:36,800 --> 01:24:38,870
- It's not decided yet.
- What exactly?

970
01:24:39,040 --> 01:24:43,113
Your acquaintance sometimes
becomes like a landmark.

971
01:24:43,280 --> 01:24:47,193
You, Savva, incarnate
a historical process.

972
01:24:47,360 --> 01:24:48,952
Which one?

973
01:24:49,120 --> 01:24:53,033
A total Exodus of the Muscovites
from communal flats to private ones.

974
01:24:53,200 --> 01:24:57,034
Wow, what eloquence!
We're moving out in a fortnight.

975
01:24:57,200 --> 01:25:00,033
Lev Evghenievich, you're
losing the game.

976
01:25:00,640 --> 01:25:03,279
Margarita Pavlovna, they
want Kostya on the horn.

977
01:25:05,440 --> 01:25:10,275
Look, my dear friends, isn't
it time for you to break up?

978
01:25:10,440 --> 01:25:11,509
Yes, of course.

979
01:25:11,720 --> 01:25:15,633
- Kostya, the phone.
- In a jiffy.

980
01:25:15,800 --> 01:25:19,634
Lev, it's a stalemate situation.
I offer you a tie.

981
01:25:21,720 --> 01:25:25,633
Khobotov, what about working a bit?

982
01:25:25,800 --> 01:25:28,030
Et si tu travaillais.

983
01:25:28,720 --> 01:25:32,793
- A preface for the Orloviches.
- All right.

984
01:25:33,520 --> 01:25:39,277
Khobotov! How is your side doing?

985
01:25:40,360 --> 01:25:42,351
Aches a bit.

986
01:25:42,800 --> 01:25:46,793
Appendix. It'll all come to this.

987
01:25:47,040 --> 01:25:51,431
- Jesus, what fantasies!
- It's all because of your skating.

988
01:25:51,880 --> 01:25:55,270
What my skating has
to do with all this?

989
01:25:55,440 --> 01:25:56,953
Some champion!

990
01:26:00,880 --> 01:26:05,635
Savva, can you put her to reason!

991
01:26:05,800 --> 01:26:09,634
- Come on, Lev.
- Are you a husband or not?

992
01:26:09,800 --> 01:26:12,792
You should've listened to me
when we were at the skating rink.

993
01:26:12,960 --> 01:26:15,633
I'm asking you for the last time!

994
01:26:15,800 --> 01:26:19,873
Only two weeks left,
have some patience, Lev.

995
01:26:27,440 --> 01:26:31,194
Ah, Anna Adamovna... But I'm
going to Armenia on a business trip.

996
01:26:31,360 --> 01:26:36,434
They've discovered on the Ararat
the wreck of the Noah Ark.

997
01:26:36,640 --> 01:26:39,438
You know already?..
Jesus, how extraordinary!

998
01:26:39,640 --> 01:26:43,349
You'll hear from me. Bye.
I'm crossing her out.

999
01:26:45,640 --> 01:26:48,632
- Hi, Soev,
- Hi, Kostya.

1000
01:26:48,800 --> 01:26:50,791
You've brought something new?

1001
01:26:50,960 --> 01:26:54,430
- Yes, and my wife liked it.
- It speaks for itself.

1002
01:26:54,640 --> 01:26:58,633
With all due respect for Mrs. Soev
and for her refined taste,

1003
01:26:58,800 --> 01:27:01,189
please, what about the finale?

1004
01:27:01,360 --> 01:27:04,511
Remember our last piece: so simple,
and with marvelous connotation?

1005
01:27:04,720 --> 01:27:08,269
- And such a scope!
- One can't please you enough.

1006
01:27:08,440 --> 01:27:12,956
The one taking the road gains smth.
Creative unrest is what you need.

1007
01:27:14,320 --> 01:27:18,199
- Soev, he is one of the audience.
- No, he's one of your neighbors.

1008
01:27:18,360 --> 01:27:23,434
But you are a poet,
a mouthpiece of the epoch!

1009
01:27:23,640 --> 01:27:26,029
- I think you're exaggerating.
- But I'm not!

1010
01:27:26,200 --> 01:27:29,272
You need creative endeavor.
You need a masterpiece!

1011
01:27:29,440 --> 01:27:31,431
Why should he need any?

1012
01:27:31,640 --> 01:27:34,438
You, an advocate of stale forms!

1013
01:27:34,640 --> 01:27:37,632
- I beg your pardon!
- You must change your appearance!

1014
01:27:37,800 --> 01:27:39,631
You have an idee fixe.

1015
01:27:39,800 --> 01:27:42,792
Look, Soev. There is another
way of self-expression.

1016
01:27:42,960 --> 01:27:45,633
Write a comedy in verse,
like Griboedov did.

1017
01:27:45,800 --> 01:27:47,711
He had a tragic end.

1018
01:27:50,480 --> 01:27:54,268
- You scare my authors away!
- The Soevs will be the end of you.

1019
01:27:54,440 --> 01:27:56,351
But who will help me? You?

1020
01:27:56,520 --> 01:28:00,115
Why not? I have a talent.

1021
01:28:01,200 --> 01:28:05,796
Lev, I've trans-lated your polka
into Russian.

1022
01:28:05,960 --> 01:28:08,030
- I can imagine.
- I'm serious.

1023
01:28:08,200 --> 01:28:09,952
Stop it, Kostya.

1024
01:28:10,120 --> 01:28:14,796
It's a song about
underprivileged youth.

1025
01:28:14,960 --> 01:28:18,794
- Oh, leave me alone.
- First the lass recollects...

1026
01:28:18,960 --> 01:28:22,635
'Ah, my Father looked askance
when he watched my polka dance.'

1027
01:28:22,800 --> 01:28:27,874
Then the lad recollects: he
had the same sad experience...

1028
01:28:28,040 --> 01:28:30,634
'Ah, my Father looked askance,
when he watched my polka dance.'

1029
01:28:30,800 --> 01:28:31,789
'Magnificent'...

1030
01:28:31,960 --> 01:28:34,793
And then he says to the girl:
come on, I know how it feels too...

1031
01:28:34,960 --> 01:28:40,796
Kostya, can you tell me, what
Margarita wants from me?

1032
01:28:41,720 --> 01:28:47,033
She wants you. It lies
in her subconscious.

1033
01:28:47,640 --> 01:28:51,349
Thus bespeaks her attraction
to the universal harmony.

1034
01:28:51,640 --> 01:28:56,953
- But this is impossible!
- Who knows.

1035
01:29:03,640 --> 01:29:06,632
Lyudochka! You've come!

1036
01:29:08,200 --> 01:29:10,350
- You're here!
- You're ill?

1037
01:29:10,520 --> 01:29:14,195
I don't know. I'm feeling blue,
staying at home...

1038
01:29:14,360 --> 01:29:16,954
My poor darling, do you want
me to make you some tea?

1039
01:29:17,120 --> 01:29:19,031
- Hi, Lyudochka.
- Hi, Kostya.

1040
01:29:19,200 --> 01:29:22,192
You heard the news?
Emile Zola died of fumes.

1041
01:29:22,360 --> 01:29:26,273
- Oh no!
- Never forget to turn off the gas!

1042
01:29:26,640 --> 01:29:29,029
Maybe you shall introduce me?

1043
01:29:29,200 --> 01:29:33,273
- Oh yes: please meet Velyurov.
- A master of eloquence.

1044
01:29:33,440 --> 01:29:37,433
Oh.
Kostya, where is Svetlana?

1045
01:29:37,640 --> 01:29:40,518
- What Svetlana?
- She is a D.Sc.

1046
01:29:42,200 --> 01:29:44,634
I'll tell you about her later.

1047
01:29:51,440 --> 01:29:53,874
- A D.Sc?
- Yes, a D.Sc.

1048
01:29:56,880 --> 01:30:01,635
Oh, it's you. Speak of the devil,
and here's the D.Sc.

1049
01:30:03,120 --> 01:30:07,033
No, you can have the book for keeps.
I'm leaving.

1050
01:30:07,200 --> 01:30:09,794
- Where?
- To look for Tamerlan's grave.

1051
01:30:09,960 --> 01:30:15,876
And thank you. What for?
'For love pangs since the day we met.'

1052
01:30:16,880 --> 01:30:22,637
What else?
'For bitter tears that I shed...'

1053
01:30:23,040 --> 01:30:26,635
- Isn't it blasphemy!
- It's just his love of poetry!

1054
01:30:26,800 --> 01:30:30,349
Thank you. I will
write you a letter.

1055
01:30:30,520 --> 01:30:35,548
What is wrong with loving Lermontov!
Or you love some other authors?

1056
01:30:35,760 --> 01:30:37,637
Bravo! What can you say to this?

1057
01:30:37,800 --> 01:30:41,634
What is wrong with my being
in love like some silly calf?

1058
01:30:41,800 --> 01:30:46,430
What is wrong with my old loves
forgotten and letters burnt down?

1059
01:30:46,640 --> 01:30:50,633
- You can't love!
- No, he can!

1060
01:30:50,800 --> 01:30:53,439
Merci, mon ange.
That was a challenge of an answer!

1061
01:30:54,280 --> 01:30:56,510
Ha, you're in concert,
the two of you.

1062
01:30:59,120 --> 01:31:02,032
Your aunt has encouraged
your corruption.

1063
01:31:02,200 --> 01:31:07,194
You can't understand: my aunt
is a wonderful creature!

1064
01:31:07,360 --> 01:31:09,635
She saw little turbulence
in her life.

1065
01:31:09,800 --> 01:31:14,351
Fiction and loneliness - this is
all she had for herself.

1066
01:31:14,520 --> 01:31:19,878
But my living here adds
turbulence to her life.

1067
01:31:20,040 --> 01:31:24,033
- And she is grateful for this.
- Ah, how kind of you!..

1068
01:31:24,200 --> 01:31:26,634
You don't sound sincere.

1069
01:32:01,640 --> 01:32:03,870
It's not funny.

1070
01:32:05,640 --> 01:32:09,030
I was always a sealed book for you.

1071
01:32:09,200 --> 01:32:13,637
After your escapade on the wedding
day, it became clear that

1072
01:32:13,800 --> 01:32:16,633
your complexity becomes you
as a pince-nez becomes Mr. Soev.

1073
01:32:18,200 --> 01:32:21,636
- I have apologized, haven't I?
- Everyone rose to the occasion.

1074
01:32:21,800 --> 01:32:25,236
And only you proved to be
everybody's antagonist.

1075
01:32:25,880 --> 01:32:28,440
Judge not that you be not judged!

1076
01:32:28,640 --> 01:32:33,634
Savransky nearly ran into a dump
truck when he learned about this!

1077
01:32:36,200 --> 01:32:39,192
Yes? Rita! I'm coming!

1078
01:32:41,440 --> 01:32:47,037
Think about your behavior and
send a wire to Sveta. She's waiting.

1079
01:33:09,640 --> 01:33:12,632
- Hey, chick, wait!..
- What a beauty!

1080
01:33:15,040 --> 01:33:19,636
'I love you, though I fret and frown,
God, what a helpless enterprise!

1081
01:33:19,800 --> 01:33:23,634
'And what a folly! How unwise!
But at your feet I'm kneeling down.'

1082
01:33:24,720 --> 01:33:27,359
We're going now to my parents.

1083
01:33:27,520 --> 01:33:33,038
You must make a favorable
impression on them.

1084
01:33:33,200 --> 01:33:35,430
I shall try my best...

1085
01:33:38,640 --> 01:33:42,952
'I'm bored without you, I yawn,
With you I feel melancholy.

1086
01:33:43,120 --> 01:33:47,636
'To tell you only this I long:
My angel, oh, how I love thee!

1087
01:33:47,800 --> 01:33:51,634
'You cast a smile - oh radiance!
Away you go - my life ends.

1088
01:33:55,640 --> 01:34:00,350
'Alina, can I entertain
A hope, the sinner as I am,

1089
01:34:00,520 --> 01:34:03,717
'For all transgressions and the pain,
Dost love you, angel, such a man?

1090
01:34:03,880 --> 01:34:10,194
'Just feign you love, put on a mask,
Play with your mimicry a game.

1091
01:34:10,360 --> 01:34:15,275
'A hope's a lie - but all the same.
Illusion - just for this I ask...'

1092
01:34:17,440 --> 01:34:23,276
You will present this perfume,
'The Beau of Moscow' - to my mom.

1093
01:34:24,280 --> 01:34:26,271
And here we are.

1094
01:34:27,040 --> 01:34:31,431
This is a critical situation!

1095
01:34:32,800 --> 01:34:35,439
Now the right forward has the ball.

1096
01:34:35,640 --> 01:34:40,714
He runs it and sends it right
into the center! Now! A goal!

1097
01:34:42,120 --> 01:34:46,033
A goal! Play, Yasha, play. A goal!

1098
01:34:46,440 --> 01:34:49,637
- Savelyich?
- What?

1099
01:34:49,800 --> 01:34:53,190
- What is the score?
- 3:2.

1100
01:34:54,960 --> 01:34:57,633
Savransky, it's 3:2.

1101
01:35:00,440 --> 01:35:02,431
Ladies, it's 3:2.

1102
01:35:05,640 --> 01:35:09,428
The stands are crowded today.
Another attack! They send a ball!

1103
01:35:11,120 --> 01:35:16,433
This duet of our forwards today
is just something!

1104
01:35:16,640 --> 01:35:19,791
We can expect any kind
of surprises from them...

1105
01:35:24,280 --> 01:35:26,271
Lev Evghenievich.

1106
01:35:32,800 --> 01:35:35,189
- Good afternoon.
- Hi.

1107
01:35:35,360 --> 01:35:38,352
- How are you feeling today?
- Fine.

1108
01:35:39,280 --> 01:35:43,717
I would like you to go with us
and have a look at our apartment.

1109
01:35:43,880 --> 01:35:46,633
- Today I can't.
- It's such a shame.

1110
01:35:47,800 --> 01:35:52,954
- But it concerns you too.
- In what way?

1111
01:35:53,640 --> 01:35:56,359
You're moving in with us.

1112
01:35:56,520 --> 01:36:00,513
Why? I have my own room here.

1113
01:36:00,880 --> 01:36:06,273
The room can wait, and it would be
better if you live with us.

1114
01:36:06,960 --> 01:36:09,520
Until you get married, of course.

1115
01:36:09,720 --> 01:36:13,269
Excuse me, but it's nonsense!

1116
01:36:14,040 --> 01:36:19,034
I talked with Savva,
he backs up my idea.

1117
01:36:19,800 --> 01:36:23,429
Savva! What does this all mean?

1118
01:36:26,520 --> 01:36:29,717
You'll be just within our reach,
it would be more expedient.

1119
01:36:32,080 --> 01:36:34,071
And you will need your room

1120
01:36:34,240 --> 01:36:37,869
when a woman shows up that
could inspire my confidence.

1121
01:36:43,640 --> 01:36:45,198
Lyudochka!

1122
01:36:54,640 --> 01:36:59,430
Margarita, Savva, please
meet my future wife.

1123
01:37:02,040 --> 01:37:07,637
Khobotov... It's not serious.

1124
01:37:08,200 --> 01:37:10,509
- I beg your pardon!
- I would better leave...

1125
01:37:10,720 --> 01:37:13,188
We shall leave together now!

1126
01:37:13,360 --> 01:37:18,639
You're not being decent
towards this girl.

1127
01:37:19,360 --> 01:37:21,351
I'm not decent?

1128
01:37:25,640 --> 01:37:27,631
I'm not decent?

1129
01:37:28,800 --> 01:37:30,472
So why say such a thing!

1130
01:37:30,680 --> 01:37:35,435
Being a complete egoist,

1131
01:37:35,640 --> 01:37:40,634
you want this girl to bear
the unbearable burden!

1132
01:37:41,040 --> 01:37:46,194
Dear, do you want all your life
go wrong,

1133
01:37:46,360 --> 01:37:48,351
turn into chaos,

1134
01:37:48,520 --> 01:37:54,117
with things vanishing: bills,
money, stockings, neckties...

1135
01:37:54,280 --> 01:37:58,637
With all electrical appliances
blowing up,

1136
01:37:58,800 --> 01:38:01,030
taking fire, breaking down!

1137
01:38:02,280 --> 01:38:05,272
With your life going
back to the lce Age,

1138
01:38:07,280 --> 01:38:12,274
but with no skins to make you warm,
because he won't get you no skins!

1139
01:38:12,520 --> 01:38:15,637
Stop it! It's all true,
I must live alone.

1140
01:38:15,880 --> 01:38:20,635
Believe me, dear, I'm not
prejudiced against him.

1141
01:38:21,280 --> 01:38:24,795
He is a flamboyant personality,
and women are attracted to him.

1142
01:38:24,960 --> 01:38:29,715
But I wouldn't mention here his
abnormal attraction to them.

1143
01:38:29,880 --> 01:38:32,633
He sends a sparkle seeing
every other woman living!

1144
01:38:32,800 --> 01:38:36,270
My whole life was
poisoned by the worst

1145
01:38:36,440 --> 01:38:39,955
and, alas, not unfounded suspicions!

1146
01:38:40,120 --> 01:38:43,192
Did he read verse to you,
spin the mist of citations?

1147
01:38:43,360 --> 01:38:45,351
Stop it! I said, it's all true!

1148
01:38:45,520 --> 01:38:49,035
So, this precious
thing here is mine!

1149
01:38:49,200 --> 01:38:52,192
He is my cross! And I will bear it!

1150
01:38:52,360 --> 01:38:55,352
You will meet another man:
more 'fresh', and more well-knit.

1151
01:38:55,520 --> 01:38:59,513
- But...
- No, Savva! She's right.

1152
01:39:20,960 --> 01:39:22,951
Forgive me, Lyudochka.

1153
01:39:24,640 --> 01:39:26,631
And farewell.

1154
01:39:26,960 --> 01:39:31,431
You... you're renouncing me?

1155
01:39:35,880 --> 01:39:39,714
I have to.
I will ruin your life.

1156
01:39:49,800 --> 01:39:51,791
It's all over.

1157
01:40:10,360 --> 01:40:12,351
It's all over...

1158
01:40:14,720 --> 01:40:16,711
It's all over.

1159
01:40:24,640 --> 01:40:26,119
Take it.

1160
01:40:38,440 --> 01:40:43,639
For the first time ever you
behaved like a grown-up person.

1161
01:40:45,440 --> 01:40:49,433
- Maybe.
- You'll be grateful to me for this.

1162
01:40:54,040 --> 01:40:59,273
'The murderer his dagger thrust,

1163
01:40:59,440 --> 01:41:02,034
'And, dying, poor De la Rue

1164
01:41:04,440 --> 01:41:07,876
Took off his hat, and said at last

1165
01:41:10,040 --> 01:41:12,031
Most gallantly: "Thank you..."'

1166
01:41:17,640 --> 01:41:19,870
What have you done?..

1167
01:41:22,640 --> 01:41:26,633
- What have I done!..
- Lev, don't be so pathetic.

1168
01:41:26,800 --> 01:41:31,794
It was like some hypnosis.
It's unbelievable!

1169
01:41:32,720 --> 01:41:34,870
With my own hands...

1170
01:41:36,640 --> 01:41:40,269
to give away happiness, hope...

1171
01:41:40,440 --> 01:41:44,433
To reject one's own
renaissance in life...

1172
01:41:44,640 --> 01:41:48,633
And all this, for fear
of some specters!

1173
01:41:48,800 --> 01:41:51,792
You behave like a child
left without his sweets.

1174
01:41:51,960 --> 01:41:54,633
- Release me!
- You psycho.

1175
01:41:54,800 --> 01:41:59,032
- I love her!
- Nonsense! Self-hypnosis!

1176
01:41:59,200 --> 01:42:01,873
- I love her!
- You, sexual maniac!

1177
01:42:02,040 --> 01:42:04,270
Savva, take a look at this baboon!

1178
01:42:04,440 --> 01:42:06,271
Hold on, Lev.

1179
01:42:06,440 --> 01:42:12,276
All my life I was thinking
with your head.

1180
01:42:12,440 --> 01:42:16,274
Now I want to be allowed
to decide for myself!

1181
01:42:16,440 --> 01:42:19,432
- It's so banal, Khobotov.
- So what!

1182
01:42:19,640 --> 01:42:23,349
lndependent intellects
never shunned banality!

1183
01:42:23,520 --> 01:42:28,958
- It's not about you!
- Yes, right you are!

1184
01:42:30,360 --> 01:42:35,275
With you out of my way I could
have become a Dostoevsky!

1185
01:42:35,440 --> 01:42:37,112
A Schopenhauer!

1186
01:42:37,280 --> 01:42:42,638
But instead I became a petty
scribbler, a walking volume!

1187
01:42:42,880 --> 01:42:46,873
All my life dawdling over
other people's prefaces!

1188
01:42:47,040 --> 01:42:49,508
Without me you would have become
everybody's punching bag!

1189
01:42:49,720 --> 01:42:52,359
A scapegoat!

1190
01:42:52,520 --> 01:42:57,036
So what! But I would
have lived! Yes!

1191
01:42:57,200 --> 01:42:58,189
Lev, zip your lip!

1192
01:42:58,360 --> 01:43:03,354
All my life constraining myself,
fearing fools and scoundrels!

1193
01:43:03,520 --> 01:43:06,876
Half-living, half-working,

1194
01:43:07,040 --> 01:43:11,511
knowing neither ups, nor downs.
Do you call this life?

1195
01:43:11,720 --> 01:43:15,269
- You ungrateful epileptic!
- I'm getting married!

1196
01:43:15,440 --> 01:43:19,558
They don't registrate nut cases!

1197
01:43:19,760 --> 01:43:21,432
You'll live and see!

1198
01:43:21,640 --> 01:43:25,428
I feel bad. I've a stitch in my side.
My head is spinning...

1199
01:43:25,640 --> 01:43:29,076
- Well, we must act!
- What are you going to do?

1200
01:43:29,240 --> 01:43:32,437
I'm calling Doctor Vera!

1201
01:43:32,640 --> 01:43:34,631
- I voice my protest!
- Don't panic.

1202
01:43:35,440 --> 01:43:39,353
- Speaking!
- It's me, Margarita!

1203
01:43:39,520 --> 01:43:42,512
- I don't have any pain!
- You will!

1204
01:43:44,800 --> 01:43:48,429
- Alice!
- Why are you shouting like that!

1205
01:43:48,640 --> 01:43:52,269
Alice, they're going to butcher me!

1206
01:43:52,440 --> 01:43:53,555
You're kidding!

1207
01:43:53,760 --> 01:43:58,880
I'm bringing Khobotov now.
His appendix acts funny.

1208
01:43:59,040 --> 01:44:03,511
What the heck! We should amputate it,
to avoid peritonitis!

1209
01:44:03,720 --> 01:44:06,712
- A progressive attitude!
- You heard it?

1210
01:44:06,880 --> 01:44:10,031
You're quite right, we should
do away with this useless tube!

1211
01:44:10,200 --> 01:44:12,430
- It's cruel!
- Hold on, Lev.

1212
01:44:14,440 --> 01:44:17,637
Arkady, go and hail a taxi.
Khobotov is going to the hospital!

1213
01:44:17,800 --> 01:44:20,792
- What's the matter?
- It's a life-or-death matter!

1214
01:44:20,960 --> 01:44:26,876
- Or you're not in shape again?
- You needn't remind me!

1215
01:44:28,440 --> 01:44:33,355
Lev, get dressed! Savva,
get his toothbrush!

1216
01:44:35,440 --> 01:44:37,635
Hey! Stop!

1217
01:44:38,960 --> 01:44:40,188
Stop!

1218
01:44:45,640 --> 01:44:47,631
- I'm not going anywhere!
- Don't offer resistance!

1219
01:44:48,040 --> 01:44:51,635
- It's violence!
- Don't let me down!

1220
01:44:51,800 --> 01:44:54,268
A D.Sc. is waiting for us
in the emergency room!

1221
01:44:55,120 --> 01:44:58,112
I'm coming!

1222
01:45:00,360 --> 01:45:04,512
I got it! I was nearly
run down by an ambulance!

1223
01:45:04,720 --> 01:45:07,518
No, I'm not going anywhere.

1224
01:45:07,720 --> 01:45:10,280
Please. Hey, give me a hand.

1225
01:45:19,200 --> 01:45:21,634
My temperature is all right.

1226
01:45:21,800 --> 01:45:25,031
The better for you. The operation
will go off smoothly.

1227
01:45:25,200 --> 01:45:28,556
Though you must admit your state
is far from being cool.

1228
01:45:29,960 --> 01:45:31,951
Hi.

1229
01:45:33,120 --> 01:45:35,111
It's some nightmare...

1230
01:45:45,720 --> 01:45:50,953
'So here I am, before all of ye,
A serious and funny guy.

1231
01:45:51,120 --> 01:45:56,877
'I make no bones of telling ye:
Who, how & what & when & why...

1232
01:45:57,040 --> 01:46:02,637
'Hey, stop the war, keep saying we.
Thus humor is a remedy...

1233
01:46:02,800 --> 01:46:08,113
'So on this warm and summer day
A monologue I'd like to say...

1234
01:46:23,640 --> 01:46:30,637
'All nature is green and blue
And so bright - Look!

1235
01:46:32,440 --> 01:46:37,036
'The spring creeks are purling
And sing every day.

1236
01:46:40,040 --> 01:46:45,034
'All life is like river
Goes on by the Spring Book.

1237
01:46:46,440 --> 01:46:52,276
'Love enters your heart,
You can't send it away.

1238
01:46:52,440 --> 01:46:55,193
'Don't send it away...

1239
01:46:59,040 --> 01:47:05,036
'Love keeping you warm,
It will not let you go.

1240
01:47:06,640 --> 01:47:12,033
'A nightingale giving
a poignant key.

1241
01:47:15,880 --> 01:47:21,637
'Love's company - sadness,
It keeps you sad. So

1242
01:47:23,640 --> 01:47:29,636
'It's better to love
Than feel melancholy...'

1243
01:48:04,440 --> 01:48:07,034
Lyudochka! Lyudochka!

1244
01:48:07,200 --> 01:48:12,638
I knew it, I believed
that you would come!

1245
01:48:20,040 --> 01:48:24,431
- Please, eat some.
- I'm not hungry.

1246
01:48:25,440 --> 01:48:30,434
- The pajama looks baggy on you...
- It's just too big for me.

1247
01:48:49,280 --> 01:48:52,272
Lyudochka, when they...

1248
01:48:52,440 --> 01:48:56,433
...when they brought me after
the operation, they dropped me!

1249
01:48:56,960 --> 01:48:58,951
I just knew it!

1250
01:48:59,120 --> 01:49:02,635
Lyudochka, I suffered a lot!

1251
01:49:02,800 --> 01:49:07,271
I was lying on that table,
naked and helpless...

1252
01:49:08,040 --> 01:49:11,032
They could do to me
whatever they wanted.

1253
01:49:12,800 --> 01:49:16,349
- Hi.
- Hi.

1254
01:49:17,640 --> 01:49:20,200
They'd never do anything wrong.

1255
01:49:20,360 --> 01:49:24,433
- Why are you so sure?
- 'cause I'm a medical worker myself.

1256
01:49:24,640 --> 01:49:29,430
I've been here for a week,
but you wouldn't come...

1257
01:49:29,640 --> 01:49:32,279
- But I didn't know!
- Yes, of course...

1258
01:49:32,440 --> 01:49:36,638
- It's all my fault.
- If it were not for Kostya...

1259
01:49:36,800 --> 01:49:42,875
Jesus, you're such a pure soul!

1260
01:49:59,800 --> 01:50:03,031
- Why don't you eat?
- I don't feel like eating.

1261
01:50:03,200 --> 01:50:09,435
'O Lord, what is my destiny:
My poor feet are failing me...'

1262
01:50:09,640 --> 01:50:11,631
Did you tell the doctor about this?

1263
01:50:11,800 --> 01:50:15,873
This is a poem by a French
poetess, which she wrote

1264
01:50:16,040 --> 01:50:19,874
when she had a baby in her womb.

1265
01:50:20,040 --> 01:50:25,956
'What's waiting for my poor baby:
Pitch darkness I'm now in maybe.

1266
01:50:26,120 --> 01:50:29,351
'So many things that I abhor:

1267
01:50:29,520 --> 01:50:33,433
'Can't drink, can't eat,
Sweet dreams not anymore...'

1268
01:50:33,640 --> 01:50:38,350
It happens. Pregnancy has
different effect on women.

1269
01:50:38,520 --> 01:50:42,035
Once a lady came to us,
she was in the family way.

1270
01:50:42,200 --> 01:50:45,510
lmagine: she was sick whenever
she saw her own husband!

1271
01:50:46,640 --> 01:50:48,631
My darling!

1272
01:50:51,200 --> 01:50:55,637
My advice: unless you're betrothed,
don't ever kiss!

1273
01:50:55,800 --> 01:50:58,633
- Getting well?
- Oh, thank you, Kostya!

1274
01:50:58,800 --> 01:51:03,032
-You gave the whole world back to me!
- Oh, you're welcome!

1275
01:51:03,200 --> 01:51:04,633
Girls, please meet each other.

1276
01:51:04,800 --> 01:51:07,030
Kostya told me a lot about you.

1277
01:51:07,200 --> 01:51:11,432
- Oh yeah, he is a talkative guy.
- My every word is a second thought!

1278
01:51:11,640 --> 01:51:12,789
- Lev Evghenievich.
- Oh yes.

1279
01:51:12,960 --> 01:51:14,632
- Khobotov.
- Margarita.

1280
01:51:14,800 --> 01:51:17,633
- What?!
- Rita.

1281
01:51:20,360 --> 01:51:25,115
Lev Evghenievich, we didn't come
alone. We have an escort.

1282
01:51:25,280 --> 01:51:28,636
- There is Savransky over there.
- Let him join us!

1283
01:51:28,800 --> 01:51:31,439
He can't leave his wheeled 'friend'.

1284
01:51:31,640 --> 01:51:34,552
Savransky, don't go away,
you may come in useful today!

1285
01:51:34,760 --> 01:51:39,436
Wow, what people come by!

1286
01:51:42,360 --> 01:51:47,718
'I told my date: let's meet again,
Because I love your pretty face.

1287
01:51:47,880 --> 01:51:53,352
'She gave a smile, and even blushed
and said: Oh yes, yes, yes!..'

1288
01:51:54,720 --> 01:51:57,359
Hi, everybody!

1289
01:51:58,720 --> 01:52:01,518
How are you? It's me!

1290
01:52:05,440 --> 01:52:07,431
- Is it all right that I came now?
- Of course!

1291
01:52:07,640 --> 01:52:09,039
It's for you.

1292
01:52:09,200 --> 01:52:12,272
You emanate triumph. Who you took
prisoner at your Austerlitz?

1293
01:52:12,440 --> 01:52:15,637
- Svetlana came to my concert.
- Don't make the same mistake.

1294
01:52:15,800 --> 01:52:17,358
Never teach fish to swim!

1295
01:52:17,520 --> 01:52:22,435
'Next day I shaved, put on a tie,
The dandy one with a polka dot.

1296
01:52:22,640 --> 01:52:27,031
'I bought three asters
And turned my step to our spot...'

1297
01:52:28,040 --> 01:52:32,352
It's a shame you don't burr.
It would make you more charming.

1298
01:52:32,520 --> 01:52:35,432
- I can do without it.
- And you should change your name.

1299
01:52:35,640 --> 01:52:38,200
Mr. Velyurov... Velour is fabric...
Make it Mr. Valour.

1300
01:52:38,360 --> 01:52:40,271
I like 'my' name!..

1301
01:52:40,440 --> 01:52:45,116
'And so we came: me - to the drugstore
Me - in cafe, in any case!

1302
01:52:45,280 --> 01:52:49,432
'Let's meet again then.
Same time, same place...'

1303
01:52:50,520 --> 01:52:53,956
I was never at the hospital: I was
at a spa. It was no picnic either.

1304
01:52:54,120 --> 01:52:58,636
The worst thing there were old women.
A discouraging spectacle!

1305
01:52:58,880 --> 01:53:02,714
- What were you doing there?
- They were probing me...

1306
01:53:02,960 --> 01:53:05,428
- Looked for you, babe.
- And me too.

1307
01:53:05,640 --> 01:53:07,949
- I was mad!
- I began to cry!

1308
01:53:08,120 --> 01:53:11,032
- You didn't come!
- Where were you?

1309
01:53:11,200 --> 01:53:13,430
- So I left!
- And so did I!

1310
01:53:13,640 --> 01:53:15,631
'And so we came:

1311
01:53:15,800 --> 01:53:19,190
' - Me - to the drugstore.
Me - in cafe, in any case!

1312
01:53:19,640 --> 01:53:23,519
'Let's meet again then.
Same time,

1313
01:53:23,720 --> 01:53:25,278
'Same place!..'

1314
01:53:27,480 --> 01:53:31,029
Lev! I am so glad!

1315
01:53:31,880 --> 01:53:33,871
Thank you.

1316
01:53:34,040 --> 01:53:37,476
- I'm so glad to see you!
- Me too.

1317
01:53:38,120 --> 01:53:42,477
Yes, I am glad to see you,
Arkady, though...

1318
01:53:44,040 --> 01:53:47,874
It hurts me to think
that you took part

1319
01:53:49,240 --> 01:53:51,231
in that act of violence...

1320
01:53:51,400 --> 01:53:55,871
I... I just wanted to help you.

1321
01:53:56,640 --> 01:53:59,871
Yeah, they literally
dragged you here.

1322
01:54:00,120 --> 01:54:06,878
Please don't. Let us
not speak about sad things.

1323
01:54:07,280 --> 01:54:10,033
Lev Evghenievich,
I learned that polka dance!

1324
01:54:11,280 --> 01:54:15,034
Mon papa ne veut pas...
Kostya, join in!

1325
01:54:15,200 --> 01:54:18,192
'When he watched my polka dance...

1326
01:54:18,360 --> 01:54:23,036
- Mon papa ne veut pas.
- When he watched my polka dance.

1327
01:54:23,480 --> 01:54:27,951
- Mon papa ne veut pas.
- Que je danse, que je danse.

1328
01:54:28,120 --> 01:54:31,874
- Mon papa ne veut pas.
- Que je danse la polka.

1329
01:54:32,040 --> 01:54:33,951
Rita, join in!..

1330
01:54:34,120 --> 01:54:36,714
I feel so bashful in her presence:
I even lose my tongue.

1331
01:54:36,880 --> 01:54:40,475
- Ah, my father looked askance.
- When he watched my polka dance.

1332
01:54:40,640 --> 01:54:44,076
- And my father looked askance.
- When he watched my polka dance!

1333
01:55:00,880 --> 01:55:04,190
- I'd better leave.
- No, you mustn't.

1334
01:55:04,360 --> 01:55:10,037
Girls, let's hide and watch
how the events unfold!

1335
01:55:10,200 --> 01:55:13,636
Lev Evghenievich, it's time
to make your choice!

1336
01:55:13,800 --> 01:55:16,872
You must fight for your rights
of a man and a human!

1337
01:55:20,120 --> 01:55:23,874
You look better today.

1338
01:55:24,040 --> 01:55:26,554
Hi, Arkady, you look magnificent.

1339
01:55:27,280 --> 01:55:32,798
- More life in your gaze.
- I feel I am all right.

1340
01:55:32,960 --> 01:55:34,871
Thanks God.

1341
01:55:35,040 --> 01:55:41,798
- How is your new apartment?
- It's all too good to be true.

1342
01:55:41,960 --> 01:55:47,478
It's so spacious! You can
swing a cat there!

1343
01:55:47,640 --> 01:55:51,792
There is some work to be done,
of course: the floors and so on.

1344
01:55:51,960 --> 01:55:56,636
Every morning I take my drill and...
Lev will like it there.

1345
01:55:56,800 --> 01:56:00,475
- Never mind that.
- But you will be living there!

1346
01:56:02,120 --> 01:56:05,795
Are you starting again?

1347
01:56:05,960 --> 01:56:09,714
The doctor said we can
take you home now.

1348
01:56:11,480 --> 01:56:14,472
What do you mean 'take' me?

1349
01:56:15,560 --> 01:56:20,270
Make all the papers ready
and get down to the vestibule.

1350
01:56:20,480 --> 01:56:22,869
Savva, grab a cab and come here.

1351
01:56:23,040 --> 01:56:26,191
- Right!
- I protest!

1352
01:56:26,360 --> 01:56:32,196
Khobotov, calm down.
It's temporary, but necessary.

1353
01:56:32,360 --> 01:56:37,798
I feel responsible to a woman
that will come one day and

1354
01:56:37,960 --> 01:56:43,114
to whom I shall entrust you, sound
and healthy and in your right mind.

1355
01:56:44,200 --> 01:56:46,191
Lev, collect your things.

1356
01:56:58,640 --> 01:57:02,474
- Savva, tell me...
- Lev Evghenievich, come on...

1357
01:57:02,640 --> 01:57:07,111
Savva dear, please tell me...

1358
01:57:07,520 --> 01:57:10,114
Will ever there be
an end to all this?

1359
01:57:11,200 --> 01:57:14,192
Why don't you answer me?

1360
01:57:14,800 --> 01:57:19,555
- Shame on you!
- What do you mean?

1361
01:57:19,800 --> 01:57:23,031
I will tell you frankly.

1362
01:57:24,800 --> 01:57:30,272
You're an outstanding man!
I look up to you!

1363
01:57:30,960 --> 01:57:35,795
You have such a clever head,

1364
01:57:35,960 --> 01:57:38,554
all these things that you know.

1365
01:57:38,720 --> 01:57:42,554
But sometimes you embarrass me.

1366
01:57:42,720 --> 01:57:45,359
- But...
- Don't interrupt me.

1367
01:57:47,480 --> 01:57:49,710
You make me feel sore, really.

1368
01:57:49,880 --> 01:57:52,474
You've such a brilliant head,

1369
01:57:52,640 --> 01:57:57,111
and with this head of yours
you can't understand obvious things!

1370
01:57:58,280 --> 01:58:02,353
You're such a lucky person!
A great woman is caring for you.

1371
01:58:02,560 --> 01:58:06,269
You can live in clover.
What else do you want?

1372
01:58:06,480 --> 01:58:09,472
You ought to be thankful
and do what you're told to.

1373
01:58:09,640 --> 01:58:13,394
You had a rest, under anesthesia,

1374
01:58:13,600 --> 01:58:18,276
but Margarita and I could hardly
have a wink of a sleep!

1375
01:58:19,960 --> 01:58:21,951
Tut, tut, Savva.

1376
01:58:22,960 --> 01:58:26,953
I thought that this hospital
here will bring you to reason.

1377
01:58:27,120 --> 01:58:30,954
And you're starting all this again.
Shame on you.

1378
01:58:31,480 --> 01:58:34,278
Can you tell me...

1379
01:58:36,040 --> 01:58:40,875
Why do you want me
to live in your house?

1380
01:58:42,720 --> 01:58:45,951
What do you personally need me for?

1381
01:58:47,720 --> 01:58:54,034
Ha, you speak foreign languages,
and you can't understand Russian?

1382
01:58:54,880 --> 01:58:58,873
It matters not what we would do
but what we should do.

1383
01:59:00,040 --> 01:59:04,113
You just won't be able to
pull through without us.

1384
01:59:05,200 --> 01:59:08,476
Why did you hammer it
into your head

1385
01:59:09,480 --> 01:59:12,472
that I will not pull
through without you?!

1386
01:59:14,800 --> 01:59:20,477
Ask Arkady. Well, it's time.
We're taking you from here.

1387
01:59:24,200 --> 01:59:25,952
It will be the end of me.

1388
01:59:27,120 --> 01:59:28,792
It's the end.

1389
01:59:30,120 --> 01:59:32,873
And what if he is right?

1390
01:59:34,880 --> 01:59:38,190
Overemotional people

1391
01:59:38,360 --> 01:59:42,273
need someone else to lead them.

1392
01:59:43,720 --> 01:59:46,280
What are you saying?

1393
01:59:46,480 --> 01:59:50,473
What on earth are you saying?

1394
01:59:51,200 --> 01:59:52,713
Kostya!

1395
01:59:53,480 --> 01:59:55,471
Kostya! Kostya!

1396
02:00:00,760 --> 02:00:07,108
It's the endspiel stage of the game
now! And I'm going to play it!

1397
02:00:08,560 --> 02:00:10,869
Savransky!

1398
02:00:15,640 --> 02:00:18,950
At last - your moment
of glory has come!

1399
02:00:19,120 --> 02:00:22,635
If they take me away,
this will be the end of me!

1400
02:00:22,800 --> 02:00:25,792
- Don't panic.
- I know what I'm talking about!

1401
02:00:25,960 --> 02:00:29,270
If they take me, there
will be no escape - ever!

1402
02:00:30,120 --> 02:00:33,874
We must elope! Now!

1403
02:00:34,040 --> 02:00:36,031
- In this pajama, you can't.
- Everything has been provided for!

1404
02:00:36,200 --> 02:00:39,272
Velyurov takes your rags, and
you're putting on his apparel!

1405
02:00:39,480 --> 02:00:40,879
What?!

1406
02:00:41,040 --> 02:00:43,031
- But the patients!
- They will not tell on you.

1407
02:00:43,200 --> 02:00:44,792
It's like a big
fellowship with them.

1408
02:00:44,960 --> 02:00:46,871
- I'm ready!
- And what about you?

1409
02:00:47,040 --> 02:00:50,112
This is some crazy farce!

1410
02:00:50,280 --> 02:00:55,274
Yes, it's a farce, a vaudeville,
a tragic comedy!

1411
02:00:55,480 --> 02:00:58,631
It's all genres together, by heck!

1412
02:00:58,800 --> 02:01:02,270
Are you an artiste or some
bath-house attendant?

1413
02:01:02,480 --> 02:01:06,109
I'm disappointed! Where is your
zest for putting on masks?

1414
02:01:06,280 --> 02:01:08,794
- Again?..
- What do you mean - 'again'?

1415
02:01:08,960 --> 02:01:12,270
You've been deluding the audience
during all these 20 years!

1416
02:01:12,480 --> 02:01:14,869
I didn't say 'no'!

1417
02:01:15,040 --> 02:01:19,477
Then hit the bushes! It's
a decisive moment for all of you!

1418
02:01:20,560 --> 02:01:25,873
I'm doing this only out of
my sympathy for Khobotov!

1419
02:01:33,200 --> 02:01:37,637
My mom is right. You're just a kid!

1420
02:01:40,120 --> 02:01:44,477
Take it easy! Youth is
a fleeting moment!

1421
02:01:46,880 --> 02:01:50,190
In no time at all I will change!

1422
02:01:50,360 --> 02:01:52,874
And not for the better!

1423
02:01:53,120 --> 02:01:56,192
I will second-guess things!

1424
02:01:57,480 --> 02:02:00,790
I will know measure in everything!

1425
02:02:02,880 --> 02:02:06,475
- Oh no.
- Don't disappoint us.

1426
02:02:06,880 --> 02:02:09,269
Yes, we're still young now!

1427
02:02:09,640 --> 02:02:13,269
I look like some cheap
rogue in this suit!

1428
02:02:13,480 --> 02:02:16,950
Hey, it's my Sunday clothes!

1429
02:02:17,120 --> 02:02:20,112
I wouldn't be too fastidious
in your place, you flannel guy.

1430
02:02:20,280 --> 02:02:21,633
They're coming!

1431
02:02:31,960 --> 02:02:34,633
Arkady Varlamovich,
it's your act now!

1432
02:02:35,480 --> 02:02:39,268
Absolute transformation!
Break your leg!

1433
02:02:39,480 --> 02:02:41,118
Oh yeah...

1434
02:02:42,720 --> 02:02:46,713
Khobotov, what do you mean?
I was waiting for you in the lobby!

1435
02:02:46,880 --> 02:02:49,030
- The taxi is here.
- Very well.

1436
02:02:49,960 --> 02:02:53,475
- What does that mean?
- It's complete 'alles kaputt!

1437
02:02:53,640 --> 02:02:57,349
A story to make one's blood freeze!

1438
02:02:57,560 --> 02:03:01,269
He was a lion disguised as a lamb!

1439
02:03:01,480 --> 02:03:04,790
I just came to visit him:

1440
02:03:04,960 --> 02:03:08,111
He dragged me into a thicket,

1441
02:03:08,280 --> 02:03:13,957
tore off my clothes and
made himself scarce!

1442
02:03:14,640 --> 02:03:18,030
'O! that this too solid flesh
would melt,

1443
02:03:18,200 --> 02:03:23,274
'Thaw, and resolve
itself into a dew!'

1444
02:03:24,800 --> 02:03:27,792
- What're you babbling about?
- Hey, it's 'Hamlet!'

1445
02:03:28,480 --> 02:03:32,109
I had to put on his rags

1446
02:03:32,280 --> 02:03:35,875
to cover my nudeness!

1447
02:03:36,040 --> 02:03:39,874
'Why, let the strucken deer go weep,

1448
02:03:40,040 --> 02:03:43,271
'The hart ungalled play;

1449
02:03:43,880 --> 02:03:47,111
'For some must watch, while some
must sleep:

1450
02:03:47,480 --> 02:03:51,871
'So runs the world away!'

1451
02:03:59,000 --> 02:04:00,991
So, you're so jubilant, eh?

1452
02:04:03,120 --> 02:04:07,033
Of course, you're quite right!

1453
02:04:07,880 --> 02:04:12,635
You doomed him to sure death!

1454
02:04:13,720 --> 02:04:16,280
Way to go, fellows.

1455
02:04:17,040 --> 02:04:21,272
Yes, I'm an evil genius,
and you're benefactors?

1456
02:04:21,800 --> 02:04:25,634
You wish him good, I wish him evil?

1457
02:04:27,960 --> 02:04:32,112
I want to tell you, Kostya.

1458
02:04:33,720 --> 02:04:37,269
Not to Velyurov, he was
just an instrument!

1459
02:04:38,280 --> 02:04:40,635
- Me? An instrument?!
- Shut up.

1460
02:04:41,560 --> 02:04:46,270
Kostya, you're too young.

1461
02:04:46,720 --> 02:04:50,110
And you can't understand
a lot of things.

1462
02:04:51,400 --> 02:04:55,632
Yes, I'm young. I've been already
reproached for this today.

1463
02:04:58,640 --> 02:05:02,633
But believe a historian:

1464
02:05:03,800 --> 02:05:09,636
you can't make one happy
against his own free will.

1465
02:05:10,280 --> 02:05:16,276
Stop it, we shall live and see,
in, say, 25 years.

1466
02:05:18,480 --> 02:05:25,113
- Where were you?
- Doing what you told me to.

1467
02:05:25,280 --> 02:05:27,874
- You fool!
- I was looking for a cab!

1468
02:05:28,040 --> 02:05:30,270
- Where is it?
- It's waiting.

1469
02:05:30,480 --> 02:05:32,710
Hurry up, we must
catch up with him.

1470
02:05:34,560 --> 02:05:38,712
To catch Savransky
is wishful thinking.

1471
02:06:32,640 --> 02:06:33,959
Lyudochka!

1472
02:06:34,120 --> 02:06:35,951
Stop!

1473
02:06:37,320 --> 02:06:38,355
Lyudochka!

1474
02:06:55,720 --> 02:06:57,631
Farewell!

1475
02:07:38,200 --> 02:07:43,115
Moscow, the 50s... They've turned
around the corner and disappeared...

1476
02:07:47,480 --> 02:07:51,712
The 60s quieted down, the 70s
fluttered away.

1477
02:07:52,480 --> 02:07:54,869
The 80s have sprouted.

1478
02:07:59,480 --> 02:08:05,112
We both, Moscow and I, change:
she is getting younger, me - older...

1479
02:08:06,120 --> 02:08:11,956
Where are you, friends of my youth?
My open-hearted girlfriends?..

1480
02:08:13,600 --> 02:08:18,196
Oh youth, did you ever exist?
And where hath you gone?..

1481
02:08:18,600 --> 02:08:23,469
Only the wind in Neskuchny Garden
sweeping up your traces...

